title: oatmeal tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Add sugars, oatmeal, salt, vanilla and pecans; mix well.
Fill miniature muffin pans 3/4 full. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
While hot, using a spoon, push mixture which has baked out over the edge back into the pan, making tart compact.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Yields 72.

title: catherine's fresh fruit pizza
directions: *(Fresh bananas, pineapple chunks, maraschino cherries, fresh oranges, peeled and cut into rounds, blueberries, strawberries and peaches.)

title: flank steak teriyaki
directions: Soak overnight.
Cook over hibachi.
Cut cross grain on a slant and into thin slices.

title: cooked squash
directions: Combine squash, seasoning, cornbread crumbs and onions.
Mix eggs and milk together before pouring over squash mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Top with cheese, if desired.
Can be covered with a lid.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cornmeal and salt.
Add butter, lemon rind, lemon juice and milk; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with a wire whisk after each addition.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy apple struedel
directions: Mix 4 cups flour and oleo as for pie crust.
Beat egg yolks and water with fork and add flour mix.
Add vinegar.
Divide sticky dough into 5 parts on wax paper.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: creamy chicken and broccoli
directions: In skillet, cook chicken in oil until browned.
In saucepan, cook broccoli until tender (do not overcook).
Add can of soup and 1/2 cup milk to chicken.
Stir.
Drain excess water from broccoli and add broccoli to chicken mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: lattice-top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, veggies, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Place in 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Unwrap crescent rolls. Separate into rectangles.
Press together perforated cuts; cut each rectangle lengthwise into 3 strips.
Place strips on casserole to form lattice top.
Bake uncovered 15 minutes longer. Top lattice with remaining cheese and onions; bake 3 to 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Preparation time:
10 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: asparagus polonaise
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over cooked asparagus.
Broil 5-inches from heat for 5 to 7 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: potato souffle
directions: Preparation time:
15 to 20 minutes.
Cooking time: about 90 minutes.

title: hamburger tater tot casserole
directions: Break
raw
hamburger
into
pieces in 9 x 13-inch pan. Season with
salt
and pepper.
Spread a thin layer of sliced onions
on top of meat.
Spread soup over this.
If you would like
it more moist, use 2 cans of soup.	Add a layer of Tater Tots.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: celery almond casserole
directions: Cut up celery in small pieces.
Cook until tender.
Add dash of salt.
Put in casserole and add chestnuts, toast almonds and layer also pimentos.
Pour soup, undiluted, over top.
Pour bread crumbs over top.
Put few pats of butter on top.
Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.

title: summer strawberry pie
directions: Mix butter, 3 tablespoons sugar and 2 cups flour in large mixing bowl with 2 knives until consistency of cracker crumbs. Divide between 2 (9-inch) pie pans.
Press mixture to form shells. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: cookie monster cookies
directions: Soften butter.
Blend butter and sugar with a fork.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in flour.
Spoon large spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: In medium saucepan, melt chocolate and butter together.
Take off heat.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook at 350° (cold oven) for 30 minutes.
Top with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda together and add alternately with buttermilk to sugar mixture. Add whole cranberries and pecans last.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or less.

title: christmas snow punch
directions: Chill ahead the punch and Sprite.
When ready to serve, combine punch and Sprite.
Add big dips of ice cream; stir. Chill.
Makes 32 servings.

title: quick cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla together.
Add flour. Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: ranch dressing cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften and add mix.
Blend together and shape into ball.
Place in refrigerator to firm up.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with coarse black pepper.

title: el rancho beef soup
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil and let simmer for at least 15 minutes.
Taste and add seasoning if needed.
Makes 10 hearty portions.
Can be frozen for future use.
The following can be added also:
potatoes, tomatoes, green chilies and garbanzo beans.

title: purple lady
directions: In large bowl dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Stir in cool whip until blended.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, onion, parsley, raisins, cashews, curry powder, pepper and mayonnaise.
Arrange lettuce on 4 plates.
Place 1/2 papaya on each plate.
Fill with 2 scoops of salad.
Salad tastes best if made a day ahead.
Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chips and cheese.
Dump in greased casserole dish and top with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cocoa cream pie
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch, egg yolks, salt and milk; cook until thick.
Stir while cooking.
Let cool, then add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
When cool, cover with meringue made by beating the egg whites, 6 teaspoons sugar and 1 teaspoon baking powder.
Beat egg whites until they begin to form, then add baking powder and then gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Put on top of pie and bake at 400° until it is a golden brown.

title: burnt sugar frosting
directions: Put 1/4 cup sugar in a heavy skillet over low heat. Stir until melted and a deep brown color.
Add water slowly while stirring. Cool.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Put first 6 ingredients
in blender on "blend" for three minutes.
Put in deep wide-rimmed 10-inch pie pan (greased). Let stand for five minutes.
Put cup of coconut on top of this. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
(Test with knife.)

title: honey lemon mustard sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients until thoroughly heated.
Serve with vegetables.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain all beans, except pork and beans and mix in large, long casserole dish.
Rinse pork and beans can out with 1/2 cup water and add to casserole.
Mix together the brown sugar, mustard and vinegar; mix thoroughly with beans.
On top of mixture, put 1/2 pound raw bacon.
Separate the onion into rings and place on top of bacon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot or cold!

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine ingredients and stir by hand for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes until it springs back to the touch.
Do not test with a toothpick!

title: oatmeal cookies 2
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add vanilla and beaten eggs. Sift dry ingredients all together, then add to sugar and shortening.
Add oats and nuts and mix together with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, approximately 15 minutes.

title: chicken chopstick
directions: Combine soup and water.
Add noodles to mixture (save 1 cup). Add chicken, celery and cashews.
Toss lightly.
Sprinkle remaining noodles on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Garnish with oranges.

title: penuchi
directions: Boil sugar and milk a few minutes.
Then add butter and boil until it forms a soft ball in water. Remove from stove and stir until it begins to grain.
Then add nut meats and vanilla.
Pour on a buttered pan and cool.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon, onion and ground round until meat is cooked through.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, covered, in any size ovenproof dish.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: barbecue chicken(mildred's way)
directions: Place on grill and brown.
Seal in foil and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour on grill or in oven.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add milk, then egg yolks.
Mix well.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly with a whisk.
Cook until thick and an indentation is left when a spoon is stirred through it.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked 9-inch crust and cover with meringue.
Brown meringue in preheated 425° oven.
Cool to room temperature before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Blend in egg, peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and quick oats. Spread in a greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: fatayer(meat pie)
directions: Combine meat, onion, yogurt, nuts and seasoning.
Place mixture on dough patties and shape into triangles.
Arrange on an oiled baking sheet and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 minutes until bottoms are lightly browned.
Broil for 5 minutes to brown tops, if needed.

title: microwaved yam
directions: Cut yam in two.
Prick with fork or paring knife.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes, turning every 2 minutes.
When done, wrap in foil and let it steam until needed.
Serves 2.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: In saucepan, bring water and raisins to boil; let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain well and set aside.
Combine scalded milk and margarine.
Slowly add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add sugar, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Place bread cubes and raisins in an 8-inch ungreased square glass dish; pour milk mixture over top, stirring to moisten.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Set glass baking dish in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: Cut meat and brown in frypan.
Take meat and next 7 ingredients, place in kettle.
Heat to boiling point.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Cut up and stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Test vegetables with fork to see if tender.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in buttered casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix and sift together 4 or 5 times. Store in airtight container. Put 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons in cup and add boiling water.

title: cinnamon bubble
directions: Place cherries and nuts in bottom of tube pan.
(Spray pan with Pam.)
Melt 1/2 stick butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Pour this over nuts and cherries.
Melt remaining 1/2 stick butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Roll frozen rolls in this mixture and place rolls in tube pan.
(Use 24 rolls; they will fit tightly around pan.)
Let rise in cold oven overnight.
The next morning, leave pan in oven; heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
This is wonderful! Turn out onto plate to serve.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients with beater until smooth.
Pour in 8-inch round pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
After, turn off oven and let pan sit in oven for 1 hour.
Remove and cool.
Then refrigerate.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Butter pan.
Slice peaches thin.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over peaches.
Slice light bread over peaches.
Mix together 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour, egg and butter.
Pour over bread.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes on 350°.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Mix first three ingredients and set aside.
Mix last four ingredients and refrigerate until ready to layer.
Pinch angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Layer angel food cake in trifle bowl, strawberry mixture, and then cool whip mixture.
Repeat. Top with strawberries.
For punch bowl, double recipe.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together eggs, cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Stir in rice, chopped onion and chillies.
Then stir in zucchini.
Pour into casserole and top with butter and grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 1 hour, until lightly browned.

title: teriyaki-grilled swordfish
directions: Also good with tuna or salmon steaks.

title: bum soup
directions: Peel potatoes; cut and quarter.
Put in a large pot; cover with water.
Peel onions, cut and quarter.
Also add to potatoes and water.
Boil until potatoes are done.
The last 15 minutes add hot dogs, cut into small bite size pieces.
Season to taste.
The more pepper the better.
Open can of milk and add to pot; just warm, do not boil.

title: cool whip frosting
directions: Combine sugar, pudding and milk in small bowl.
Beat slowly 1 minute.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread on cake.
Good on angel food.

title: mexican beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add soup, tomato sauce and paste, green chiles and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.

title: fruit cake
directions: Put fruit in large pan; add raisins and nuts.
Sift flour over this.
Add all spices, soda and salt to the flour.
(If using self-rising flour, omit salt and soda.)
With hands, mix the flour and spice mixture with the fruit until every piece of fruit is covered.
Add sugar, oil, molasses, eggs and grape juice; mix well.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup cake mix.
Mix the rest of the cake mix with the margarine and 1 egg.
Crumble and pat in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix 2/3 cup cake mix with corn syrup, 4 eggs, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes with electric beater.
Pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: one-dish dinner with chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Put rice in flat ovenproof dish; top with soup.
Add small amount of water.
Season chicken with salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Place over rice and soup mixture.
Top with celery, parsley and ginger.
Cover with foil; bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Uncover; add additional water
if necessary.
Broil to brown chicken.

title: ozark pie
directions: Mix all
the
ingredients well.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch pan and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir in shortening.
Drop into mixture of 3 tablespoon sugar and 2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spicy nacho dip
directions: Melt cheese in microwave or double boiler.
Add melted cheese to Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies.
Mix. Serve as a warm dip for tortilla chips.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Add all the ingredients, beat with mixer.
Makes 1 quart. Good in refrigerator 2 to 3 months.

title: david's casserole
directions: Brown in skillet, ground beef, onion.
Add enchilada sauce, Cream of Mushroom soup, Cream of Chicken soup, chopped green chilies.
Cut tortilla in wedges and put layer on bottom of large casserole dish.
Use enough of above mixture to cover and add another layer of tortilla wedges.
Repeat until all of sauce is used.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350 for about 30 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Mix and warm for 3 hours in a crock-pot.
Serve hot.

title: meringue
directions: Beat the egg whites on moderately high speed until soft peaks are formed.
Add the Marshmallow Creme and beat until firm, but moist peaks are formed.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy on high speed.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Mix until smooth.
Pour mixture in graham cracker crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill 3 hours before serving.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Lay in layers in greased pan.
Top with buttered crumbs. Crumbs can be used between layers if desired.
Bake till warm at 350°.

title: angel food cake
directions: Measure sifted flour, add 1/2 cup sugar.
Sift together 4 times.
Combine egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and flavorings in large bowl.
Beat with sturdy beater until moist soft peaks form.
Add rest of sugar in 4 additions, beating until blended each time.
Sift in flour mixture in 4 additions, folding in with large spoon each time; turn bowl often.
Bake
at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Melt margarine and let cool.
Beat eggs; add flour, sugar, salt and pineapple.
Mix well.
Mix in cooled, melted margarine and cubed bread.
Put in quart casserole and bake at 350° for about an hour or until browned.
Good with ham.
A good pot-luck dish.
(Conversation casserole.)

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until done.
When it's cool enough to handle, cut into bite size pieces.
In a large, deep baking dish, put 1 cup of broth from the boiled chicken.
Put chicken into the broth.
Add cream of chicken soup, undiluted, on top of chicken and spread evenly.
Mix margarine, flour and milk.
Mix evenly to be sure there are no lumps in batter.
Pour over the other ingredients. Cook at 350° until batter forms a crust.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Melt oleo and beat together with oil, sugars, eggs and vanilla with mixer.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Add to first mixture about 1/3 at a time.
Dough will be very soft.
Chill 2 or 3 hours or overnight.

title: john's favorite meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; shape into a loaf pan.
Bake at least 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Poke holes in bottom pie crust and bake 10 minutes.
Drain Veg-All juice into saucepan and set vegetables aside.
Add bouillon cube, spices and chicken chunks.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer on low until chicken is cooked.
Add cream of chicken soup and simmer about 3 minutes until soup softens and blends.
Remove from heat and add Veg-All vegetables. Stir slightly.
Empty into bottom pie crust.
Roll out 1 pie crust between wax paper (for the top).
Put top on pie and poke holes in it.
Bake until top crust is desired brownness.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in a loaf pan and bake at 400 for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Make paste of coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture.
Add salt, flour, buttermilk and vanilla. Beat.
Fold in vinegar and soda.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put into 2 layer cake pans.

title: artichoke heart rice
directions: Prepare the rice.
Add the next 4 ingredients to the rice. Combine the mayonnaise and the oil from the artichokes and blend well.
Add to the rice mixture.
Chill and serve garnished with sliced tomato wedges and black olives.

title: ruth neidlinger's welsh cookies
directions: Mix and sift flour, nutmeg, soda, salt and baking powder. Cut in sugar and shortening.
Add currants, then add eggs and milk.
Roll out as pie dough and cut with round cookie cutter. Bake in an electric frypan, the same as pancakes, for about 3 minutes on each side, or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with sugar while still warm.

title: sugarless ice cream
directions: Put small amount of milk in saucepan with flour.
Heat, add egg yolks slowly, stirring constantly to prevent curdling; set aside. Mix pudding mix with Cool Whip, milk, vanilla and Equal.
When milk, flour and egg yolk mixture gets cool, mix everything but egg whites.
When this is mixed, fold, don't stir, in beaten egg whites; if not sweet enough, add Sweet and Low.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chocolate marshmallow  cookie pie
directions: Microwave marshmallows and 2 tablespoons of milk in medium bowl on High 45 seconds.
Stir.
(Marshmallows will be partially melted.)
Refrigerate 15 minutes to cool.
Stir in 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Pour 2 cups milk into large bowl.
Add pudding.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute or until thickened.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Arrange cookies over pudding mixture.
Spread marshmallow mixture over cookies.
Refrigerate 4 hours until set.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Add apples to top.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Pour water over.
Mix flour, sugar and butter with fingers until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: blue-ribbon tamale pie
directions: In a heavy 10-inch frying pan with ovenproof handle, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon on absorbent paper; reserve. Saute 3 minutes in bacon fat the onion and garlic.
Add beef and saute until brown, breaking meat up with a fork as it cooks.
Stir in tomato soup, chili powder, salt and paprika.
Heat to blend flavors.
Spoon meat mixture into bowl; reserve.

title: luncheon fettuccini alfredo
directions: Saute mushrooms in a little butter.
Stir in ham.
Add cooked noodles, cheeses and whipping cream, stirring until cheese melts. Serves 8 and is an easy, quick dish.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Roll into ball.
Then roll into finely ground nuts, either pecans or walnuts.
I like walnuts the best.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease pan.

Spread the pineapple, then cherry pie filling, then yellow cake mix and then melted oleo; top with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or bake at 325° for 1 hour before sprinkling pecans on top and bake another 15 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding in mixer.
Add Cool Whip.
Place a layer of graham crackers, layer of pudding, layer of graham crackers, layer of pudding and layer of graham crackers.
Ice with Dutch chocolate icing.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pies
directions: Add ingredients, mixing as you go. Bake in unbaked shell 35 minutes or until brown at 325°.

title: refrigerator fruit cake cookies
directions: Crush wafers.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs to roll logs in.
Add all other dry ingredients.
Drizzle milk over ingredients.
Form in logs.
Roll logs in wafer crumbs.
Store in refrigerator. Remove when logs are firm and slice to eat.

title: yum-yum casserole
directions: In large skillet, mix hamburger, salt, sugar, oregano, ketchup and onion.
Cook and drain off fat.
Add cheese and tomato soup. Add to cooked macaroni and reheat.

title: cranberry-pineapple molded salad
directions: Place pineapple and relish in sieve over measuring cup. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir until all is dissolved. Add orange juice or water to juice drained from pineapple and relish to make 2 cups; add to gelatin mixture.
Stir in drained pineapple and relish and place in 2-quart mold or serving dish. Chill until firm, at least 4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine corn with remaining ingredients and boil 15 minutes. Pack into sterilized Kerr jars to within 1/2 inch of top.
Put on cap.
Screw band firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large baking dish.
Add soups, rice and water.
Arrange seasoned pork chops on top and cover.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 45 more minutes.

title: chocolate cream filled angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix, bake and cool cake as directed on box.
After placing cake on serving plate, slice a 1-inch layer from the top and set aside.
Cut around cake 1 inch from outer edge down to 1 inch from bottom, then cut around cake 1 inch from inner edge down to 1 inch from bottom.
Gently pull out the cake between cuts, leaving a 1-inch layer on the bottom; tear the removed cake into small pieces.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain apricots and pineapple, saving juice.
Mix apricots, pineapple, jello, hot water and 1 cup combined apricot/pineapple juice.
Top with miniature marshmallows.
Chill until firm.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar; set aside.
Mix together milk and pudding; add Cool Whip.
Add gradually to cream cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Line bottom of flower pot with foil to plug holes.
Place about 1 1/2 inches cookie crumbs in bottom.
Add a layer of pudding mixture, layer of cookie crumbs, layer of pudding, etc.
End with about 1 1/2 inches crumbs.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Decorate with artificial flowers.
Serve with toy shovel and gummy worms on the side.

title: egg pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar, butter and meal.
Mix in vinegar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Pour in pie shell and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: String, break and wash beans.
Put in boiling, salted water with a small piece of bacon or bacon grease.
I use oil.
Cook until tender, about 45 minutes.
Let water cook out.

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Heat milk to lukewarm; add oil, honey and salt.
Stir together and add whole wheat flour.
Add yeast and eggs; beat well.
Let rise in warm place 15 minutes. Punch down; add remaining flour and knead for a few minutes.
Pat out to 12-inch square and cut into 2-inch squares.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise in warm place 10 minutes.
Bake 12 minutes at 425°.

title: baked cavatelli
directions: Prepare pasta according to directions.
In large skillet cook sausage until no pink remains.
Remove from skillet, reserving 1 tablespoon fat.
Cook green onions and garlic in drippings.
In 2-quart casserole combine pasta, sausage, onion mixture, tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce, 1/2 of cheese, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Toss to combine.
Bake covered in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake additional 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pan-fried onion dip
directions: Peel and thinly slice onions. Saute the onion in the butter and oil until the onions are caramelized, about 30 minutes. Cool. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill for 1 hour. Serve dip with vegetables, chips or crackers. Makes 1 3/4 cups of dip.

title: kay's berried delight
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Beat together cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip. Spread over crust.
Put berries on top.
Mix pudding and 2 1/2 cups cold milk as package directs.
Pour over berries.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill several hours or overnight.
May freeze for later use.

title: tuna and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles in unsalted water and drain.
Mix with all other ingredients, except potato chips.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with potato chips and more cheese if desired. Bake at 400° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry crunch cake
directions: Drain strawberries, reserve syrup and set aside.
Cream together butter or magarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Blend in sour cream.
Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Spread half of the batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spoon drained strawberries atop batter. Combine chopped walnuts, brown sugar, sugar and ground cinnamon. Sprinkle half the nut mixture atop strawberries.
Spread remaining batter over all.
Sprinkle with remaining nut mixture.
Bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes.
In small saucepan, combine cornstarch and the reserved strawberry syrup.
Heat and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add lemon juice.
Cool.
Serve over warm or cool cake.
Top each serving with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: city chicken
directions: Thread pork on small wooden skewers.
Combine flour, garlic, salt and pepper on a plate; roll kabobs in flour mixture until coated.
In a large skillet, heat butter and oil over medium heat. Brown kabobs, turning frequently; drain.
Sprinkle with soup mix. Add broth and water.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until tender.
Remove kabobs and keep warm.
If desired thicken the pan juices and serve over mashed potatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: german cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Cream remaining butter with cream cheese until softened.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Blend in 1 egg, 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Set aside.
Beat remaining eggs until thick and light in color.
Gradually add remaining 3/4 cup sugar, beating until thickened.
Add baking powder, salt and remaining 1/2 cup flour.
Blend in cooled chocolate mixture, nuts, almond extract and remaining 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Measure 1 cup chocolate batter and set aside.
Spread remaining batter in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Top with cheese mixture.
Drop measured chocolate batter from tablespoon onto cheese mixture.
Swirl with spatula to marble.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 13-inch) baking dishes.
Divide batter in half and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Crust will be about 1-inch thick.
While cake is baking, mix 1 cup evaporated milk and sugar; bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved; add coconut. Pour mixture over the 2 cakes.
In another pan, mix the 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and 1 stick oleo.
Heat to rapid boil and remove from heat; add chocolate chips, stir until melted. Stir in the nuts.
Drizzle chocolate mixture over other mixture already on the two cakes.
Spread as quickly as possible.

title: lime pie
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions for quick-set. Beat cream cheese and gradually add jello mixture.
Pour into pie shell and chill (at least 1 hour).
Add whipped topping and serve. Almost fat and sugar-free.

title: saltine pie
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff. Combine remaining ingredients and fold in egg whites. Bake in 9-inch pie pan 30 minutes at 350°. Top with ice cream, crushed fruit or chocolate sauce.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain and put in a large bowl.
Add taco mix, picante sauce and tomato paste, mixing well.
Put 1/2 of the mixture in each pie crust.

title: big red cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Bake and cool.
Punch holes in cake.
Mix Jell-O with hot water and Big Red.
Pour over cake. Prepare pudding according to directions.
Pour on top.
Add Cool Whip on top of pudding.

title: haluski
directions: Chop cabbage and onion. Melt 1/4 lb. Butter in large skillet. Put in 1/4 chopped cabbage, onion, salt and pepper. Fry and stir until brown on medium heat. Repeat with remaining ingredients. Cook noodles as directed on package. Drain and mix with cabbage. Can be frozen.

title: reese's cups
directions: Heat on low temperature until melted and smooth.
Use a spoon and dip each ball into melted chocolate.
Place each dipped ball onto a wax paper lined cookie sheet until chocolate hardens. Store in an airtight container.

title: paige's easy sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs well until blended. Stir in cooking oil, vanilla and lemon rind. Blend in sugar until thickens. Sift together flour and baking powder; stir in. Bake at 350° until done. Cookies are soft.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix with electric mixer until well mixed.
Shape into a ball and place on waxed paper.
Roll in chopped nuts.
For variety, add garlic, onions, deviled ham and bacon bits.
Use your imagination. It's great!

title: freezer slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and cover with salt.
Add Sweet 'N Low.
Let stand 1 hour and squeeze out the water; add green pepper and celery to cabbage.
Simmer the remaining ingredients for 15 minutes.
Add to the squeezed out cabbage; cover in tight bowl.
Will keep for weeks in refrigerator or put in bags and freeze as desired.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, pumpkin, flour, soda and cinnamon. Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Pour mixture onto the jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: stuffed apricot french toast
directions: Use microwavable roasting rack or cookie sheet and spray lightly with nonstick cooking spray.
Wash and slice unpeeled potatoes as thin as possible, 1/8-inch or less.
Russet or new potatoes work well.
Only slice what will fit on one cooking tray, usually one medium-sized potato.
Place slices of potato on sheet in a single layer.
Leave plain or sprinkle with any seasoning like salt-free Mrs. Dash, Lawry's seasoned lite salt, granulated garlic or powder, granulated onion or powder, or mix your own.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes on High (100% power), uncovered, until the potatoes turn light brown.
Rotate the cooking tray once if the potatoes are cooking unevenly.
More time may be required if they are wet or if a larger cooking tray is used.
Cool after cooking and store in Ziploc bags.
Will keep well 2 to 3 weeks or more.

title: super spaghetti
directions: In a skillet, brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain fat.
Add onion, green pepper and seasonings.
In large pot, slow cook the spaghetti sauce and add pepperoni.
Cook spaghetti noodles.
Add hamburger and sausage mixture to sauce.
Simmer to let the flavors blend.
Serve.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Crumble breads; add all other ingredients except margarine. Pour into crock-pot. Dot with margarine. Cover and cook on HIGH for 2 hours or on LOW for 3 to 4 hours. Makes 16 servings, 6 ounces each.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Mix bread crumbs with seasonings and cheese.
Shape veal into 4 or 5 patties.
Dip in egg, then bread crumb mixture.
(Bread twice for nice coating.)
Fry in small amount of oil until brown. Bake in covered skillet for 25 minutes at 350°.
Drain off any fat.
Cover with sauce; bake 30 minutes longer.
Put a slice of Mozzarella cheese on each veal patty and bake 5 minutes longer, or until melted.
Serve with spaghetti and sauce.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix lemon drink mix, sugar and water; add pineapple juice and chill.
In punch bowl, place lime sherbet; pour mix over sherbet and add chilled ginger ale, 7-Up or Sprite.

title: cream cheese and cucumber sandwiches
directions: Peel cucumbers; remove seeds and thinly slice and chop. Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Serve on dark brown bread, or for finger sandwiches spread on white bread.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples and spices.
Place on bottom crust.
Cover with top crust.
Cut holes in top of pie.
Sprinkle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes and at 350° for an additional 30 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the egg yolks and 1/3 cup buttermilk.
Mix the dry ingredients together.
Add to the other mixture, part at a time, beating after each addition.
Add the other 1/3 cup buttermilk, bananas and nuts.
Add the beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 layers or a loaf pan, 9 x 13-inch, at 325° approximately 1 hour.
Frost with your favorite icing.

title: zucchini snack cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl. Stir in oil, vanilla and eggs.
Add zucchini, raisins and 1 cup nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle top with remaining 1/2 cup nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chocolate syrup.
Take 1 1/2 cups of this mixture and add the syrup to it.
Pour green mixture in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan and then pour in chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix together buttermilk and pudding.
Drain all fruits.
Then mix together all ingredients.

title: chewy pecan squares
directions: Put eggs and brown sugar into double boiler and steam for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from fire and while hot add the biscuit mix, chopped pecans, cream or evaporated milk and vanilla.
Bake in a well-greased pan, 10 x 10 x 2 inch in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm and roll in powdered sugar.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan.
Crumble nuts into bottom of pan.
Put cake mix, rum, pudding, water, oil and eggs into bowl and mix together for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into cake pan and bake 60 minutes at 325°.
Remove cake from oven and immediately pour or spoon hot glaze over it.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Brown ground beef.
Stir in water, margarine and hash browns. Heat to boiling over high heat until margarine is melted.
Reduce heat to medium high, press beef and hash browns down evenly.
Cook uncovered, do not turn or stir until liquid is absorbed and bottom is brown.
Cut small sections and turn sections to continue browning.
Press firmly and continue cooking about 2 minutes or until brown.
Remove from heat.
Stir milk and cheese together and pour over the top.
Do not mix together.

title: steven's big fat cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet with shortening.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and put in pan.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and put on top of the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple (if desired, may add juice).
Mix all together and chill several hours before serving.
Delicious alone or with a pound cake.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Press on chopped nuts if desired and chill before serving.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients except lettuce; toss to mix.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package and drain.
Add vegetables, seasonings and dressing; toss thoroughly and coat vegetables well.
Chill in refrigerator at least 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a double boiler, melt the chocolate. In a bowl, sift together the cocoa powder, baking powder and flour.
In another bowl, cream the butter with the sugar until very light.
Add dry ingredients and the orange juice, alternating 1/3 of each at a time.
Blend in the melted chocolate.
Fold in the egg whites.

title: cinnamon honey spread
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Chill for 20 minutes.
Yield:
Approximately 1 cup.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat the broiler.
Place sausage in a large, deep skillet. Cook over medium high heat until evenly browned.
Drain and transfer to a medium bowl.
Blend cream cheese with the sausage. Stuff mushroom caps with the cream cheese and sausage mixture. Arrange on a baking sheet.
Broil for 2 - 3 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.

title: chicken dip
directions: Mix all together with electric mixer and chill.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: almond cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, 4 tablespoons cornstarch, water and salt in double boiler.
Cook 10 minutes after mixture turns transparent. Whip egg whites until stiff.
Add almond flavoring.
Add this mixture to cornstarch mixture, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Put in baked pie shell.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and soak 3 hours in 1-quart water with 2 trays of ice, stirring occasionally.
Mix remaining ingredients together as a pickling syrup.
Drain vegetables.
Combine with syrup in stainless steel or enameled kettle and heat, just to boiling.
Seal in hot jars.
Makes approximately 8 pints.

title: squash puppies
directions: Cook squash until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain.
Mash and drain again.
Combine squash and remaining ingredients.
Drop mixture by tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: tassies
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and flour overnight in bowl.
Mold dough into small cupcake pan and press middle down.
Fill with remaining ingredients after they are mixed together well.
Put 1 teaspoon of filling in each pastry lined cup.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries on paper towels.
Mix butter, Marshmallow Creme, powdered sugar, almond extract and dash of salt. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Then pat out small amounts of the white mixture in hand and place a cherry in the center and roll up into balls.
Place them on a greased cookie sheet and refrigerate 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and cover balls.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion and celery in 2 teaspoons vegetable oil until limp.
Add remaining ingredients, exception imitation bacon bits and heat to boiling, but do not boil. Sprinkle with imitation bacon bits.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt together sugar and butter until creamy.
Beat in eggs and flour.
Blend in cocoa, vanilla and walnuts.
Combine thoroughly. Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with marshmallows.
Cover pan with foil.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes or until marshmallows can be spread evenly.

title: candy cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients except 1/4 stick of wax and chocolate chips and roll into bite size balls.
Melt chocolate and wax over double boiler.
Dip balls into mixture and place in refrigerator until cool.

title: joe's white christmas fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover and boil for 3 minutes.
Uncover and cook, without stirring, until mixture registers 230° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat.
Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry spread
directions: Cook until blueberries are smooth.
Put on pancakes, bread, etc.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Put cucumbers and onions in sealable bowl.
Add 1/4 cup mayonnaise and 1/4 cup sour cream to cucumbers and onions along with vinegar.
Mix well.
Mixture should be thin, for moisture from cucumbers will add additional liquid.
Depending on tartness desired, quantities of mayonnaise, sour cream and vinegar may be varied.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger
meat	and onion.
Add tomatoes, beans and rice.
Put in
a
baking dish and cover with cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minute at 350°.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in short, narrow strips and toss with soy sauce. Brown on 1 side in oil.
Add green pepper.
Stir and cook until meat is browned.
Combine water and cornstarch.
Add to meat and cook until peppers are tender and sauce is thickened.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chili mac
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion in oil in a skillet. Add tomato and kidney beans.
Combine salt, pepper, chili powder, sugar, vinegar and water.
Stir into meat mixture.
Add dry macaroni and mix well.
Cook on high until steaming freely, then simmer for 40 minutes.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Don't add water.
Simmer until celery is tender.

title: diabetic jello salad
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan; refrigerate until set.

title: peanut butter brittle
directions: Lightly butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1 cup peanut butter chips evenly over bottom of pan; set aside.
In 2 1/2-quart pan, melt butter; add sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly to hard crack stage (300° to 310°). Remove from heat; stir in peanuts.
Immediately spread mixture evenly into prepared pan, being careful not to disturb chips. Quickly sprinkle remaining peanut butter chips and chocolate chips over candy.
Cool completely.
(I put it in refrigerator).
Break into small pieces and store in tightly covered container.

title: braciole di maiale(italian style loin chops)
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter or margarine in a pan.
Add the onions that have been sliced into thin rings.
Let them wilt, but make sure they do not become golden.
In a frying pan, brown the pork loin chops on both sides with the remaining tablespoon of butter, salt and pepper.
Place the loin chops on the bed of onions in a baking dish.
Place on each chop a slice of Swiss cheese and the diluted tomato sauce, together with pats of butter. Cover with aluminum foil.
Place in hot oven for 40 minutes. Serves 2.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini.
Combine dry ingredients and add to zucchini and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: corn souffle
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs and add.
Add all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Sift together.
Beat 1 egg into 1 1/2 cups applesauce.
Add to dry ingredients with 2 tablespoons oil or melted shortening.
Nuts may be added if desired.
Bake in loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in the cobbler pan in the oven as it preheats to 350 degrees. Mix the flour, sugar and milk into a batter. Pour batter over melted butter. Add berries or fruit of any kind (ie: peaches, apples, cherries, strawberries, etc.) Cook until brown on top and solid in the center.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bones and cut into chunks; set aside.
Brown onion in butter; cook on low heat.
Add pimento and soups.
Cook 5 minutes on low heat.
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
When done, layer each of the following in a casserole dish:
noodles, chicken, soup mixture, with cheese last.
Repeat layering.
Heat and serve.

title: baked sandwich(great for brunch)
directions: Place 6 slices in buttered baking sheet.
Layer cheese over bread.
Brush with mustard.
Arrange ham over cheese.
Butter one side of remaining bread slices.
Place buttered side up over ham.

title: individual cherry cheesecakes
directions: Place foil liner in muffin pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add eggs.
Beat until well blended and creamy.
Put 1 wafer in each foil liner. Pour over vanilla wafer (3/4 full) cheese mix.
Bake 25 minutes; let cool.
Top with any pie filling (cherry, jam, chocolate shavings, etc.).

title: lasagna
directions: Remove sausage from outer casing; chop meat.
Saute sausage, beef, onion and garlic until brown.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon salt, basil leaves, fennel seed, pepper and half of parsley; mix well. Add tomatoes, tomato paste and 1/2 cup of water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer until thick, 1 1/2 hours.
Cook lasagna. Drain.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry the bacon, break up into small pieces.
Add bacon to the ham and a little bit of the bacon grease.
To this add onion, green pepper and mushrooms; shake in desired amounts of soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Let this simmer while you cook the rice.
Cook rice until almost done, rinse in hot water and drain. Add the rice to the bacon mixture.
Scramble the eggs, cook them until done and light.
Spoon the eggs into the rest of the mixture.
Eat hot.

title: apple cake pie
directions: Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan for 40 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add with buttermilk to flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Turn onto floured board, adding more flour if necessary to roll out without sticking.
Roll to a 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in rounds.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes, until golden brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Mix other ingredients except bacon.
Pour into baking dish.
Place bacon on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar and salt and about half of flour.
Beat 2 minutes with an electric beater.
Add egg and shortening, then beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Drop by teaspoonfuls over greased 9-inch pans. Sprinkle topping on and cover; put in warm place until double. Heat oven to 375°.
Bake until brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Cut cabbage, onion and sweet pepper into small pieces.
Place in a large bowl.
Add sugar, salt, celery seed and mustard seed. Pour vinegar over all and stir.
Store in covered bowl in refrigerator.
This will keep 10 to 14 days.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Slice strawberries and cover with 1/2 cup sugar.
Break angel food cake into small pieces in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar with mixer.
Add Cool Whip and blend well. Spread over top of cake pieces.
Add strawberries to glaze and pour all over cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix well.
Form balls (small) and roll in powdered sugar. Keep in an airtight container.
If moist, add more powdered sugar.

title: divinity pie
directions: Beat egg whites with mixer until frothy and add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff, gradually adding in the sugar.
Add crackers by folding in only.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a well buttered 9-inch pie plate for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and put 8 ounces of Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with coconut (optional).

title: pecan diamonds
directions: Beat the 1/3 cup butter and 1/4 cup sugar. Beat in egg.
Stir in all-purpose flour. Press into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
(Dough may be thin.)
Cook in oven preheated to 375° for 12 minutes.

title: baby plum cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs; mix.
Add oil, vanilla and plums.
Beat with mixer until smooth; add nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Prunes can be substituted for plums.
Very good with caramel icing.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Shell raw shrimp; devein.
Sprinkle shrimp with lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Add 1 teaspoon salt; set aside.
Melt butter in large skillet; add onion, green pepper and garlic. Saute over low heat, about 5 minutes or until tender.
Blend flour, celery salt, salt, pepper, chili powder and Tabasco sauce and combine tomatoes and ketchup.
Heat 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sausage and cook for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until lightly pink.
Serve over rice.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Bake on top shelf at 350° for 1/2 hour or more.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: ground beef and vegetable casserole(takes twenty minutes to cook)
directions: Put ground beef and onion into a heavy pot or Dutch oven. Brown over medium heat, stirring.
Add celery, carrots, parsnip and cabbage.
Cook until meat is no longer pink and vegetables have begun to get tender, about 5 minutes.
Add broth, rice, salt and oregano.
Stir, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve garnished with parsley.

title: good punch
directions: Mix all together in gallon container.
Add 1 quart ginger ale or 7-Up.
Chill if need be.
Serves 20.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix well and freeze in a loaf pan.
To serve, slice and serve frozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add eggs and corn; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stained glass salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges. Mix ingredients together. Do not thaw strawberries. Chill and serve. Makes 10 servings.

title: white chocolate pound cake
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine evaporated milk and chocolate. Cook and stir over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Cool to room temperature.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine the flour, baking soda and salt; add to the creamed mixture, alternately with chocolate mixture.
Beat just until combined. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack; cool completely.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Brown chicken and green pepper in oil; add salsa, broth and corn.
Bring to boil.
Add rice, cover and let set 5 minutes. Grate 1/2 cup cheese, cover and let set 2 minutes.
(We like it better with less rice.)

title: bierocks
directions: Preheat oven to 350 F.
Brown ground beef and onion in a large skillet, drain.
Add cabbage and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add soup mix and pepper, set aside.
Roll one loaf of bread dough into a 16 x 8 inch rectangle, then cut into eight 4 inch squares. Spoon mixture into center of each square, bring up diagonal points, pinching edges closed.
Turn square upside down on cookie sheet sprayed with cooking spray.
Let rise for 15 minutes.
Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.
makes 16 bierocks.

title: elisabeth's cheese cake
directions: Mix together.
Line bottom and sides of cheese cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: russian tea cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine all ingredients and mix well by hand. Do not use a mixer. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool before serving.
Delicious!

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain and cool.
Add chopped ingredients.
Stir to mix.
Add canned ingredients.
Stir to mix.
Add defrosted peas and dressing (made to directions on package).
Stir all well.
Chill 6 to 8 hours.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: In a saucepan, put margarine and cream cheese.
Heat until mixture is warm enough to stir in the powdered sugar.
Spoon over the top of the cake mix.

title: pork chops & gravy
directions: Wash pork chops.
Tenderize the chops with meat tenderizer, garlic, onion powder, salt & pepper.
Fry chops in 1 can of beer until done.
Add cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: choco brownie cake
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil.
Sift next 3 ingredients together.
Mix next 3 ingredients together.
Add all together; stir well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with any sour cream chocolate frosting.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Mix flour and sugar on board.
Put butter on board and gradually work in dry ingredients kneading well.

After all ingredients are worked together knead and press into oiled and floured mould. If you do not have a mould, you may just shape it with your hands and pat down firmly. Remove from mould and place on tray lined with baking paper. Bake for about 2 hour at oven temperature 300 degrees.
You may use 1 cup white flour and 1 cup rice flour.

title: easy 3 step chicken
directions: I use chicken breasts; this will cover 8 to 10 breasts.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, drain and set aside.

title: refrigerator angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add eggs, buttermilk and yeast water all at once.
Just mix until flour is moist.
Refrigerate.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake biscuits at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cover with plastic wrap while dough is stored in refrigerator.
Can be kept and used to make "fresh hot biscuits" for a week or more.

title: meat loaf(prize winning recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ground beef.
Mix well.
Add beef.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Shape and press in 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: juniorette salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, drain and rinse; set aside.
Shred cabbage fine.
Dice onion and cucumber.
Remove seeds from green pepper and chop.
Mix ingredients together and toss.

title: serviceberry nut stuffing
directions: Soak berries in hot water for 2 hours.
Drain well.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Use for stuffing wild fowl.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onions; drain.
Combine soup and sour cream; stir in carrots.
Fold in zucchini and onions.
Mix dressing with margarine.

title: depression crackers
directions: Line a 15 X 10 X 1 cookie sheet with foil.
Put crackers on cookie sheet.
Melt butter and add sugar, boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat add vanilla.
Pour over crackers and spread. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 10 minutes at 350.
When cool break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: sun jar cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Put them in a jar.
Depending on the jar size, use 1/2 to 1 cup of vinegar.
Add other ingredients.
Add water to rim.
Place rye bread on top.
Cover with plastic top or wrap with Saran Wrap and rubber band. Leave in sun for 3 days (minimum) or until cucumbers turn light.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco, add margarine and cream well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add milk 1/3 cup at a time and beat each time.
Add flour, small amount at a time, mixing well. Add vanilla.
Pour mixture into ungreased tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn oven to 325° and bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: creamy zucchini quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spread bottom of pastry shell with mustard and bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Reduce heat of oven to 350°. Place zucchini in colander; sprinkle with salt and drain about 5 minutes.
While zucchini is draining, saute mushrooms in butter. Sprinkle one cup of the grated cheese into the bottom of the pastry shell.
Spoon mushrooms on top.
Squeeze zucchini to remove the last bit of moisture and put into pastry shell, separating and fluffing with fingers.
Beat together cream cheese, cream, egg yolks and whole egg.
Season with salt and pepper.
Set pastry dish on baking sheet and carefully put in cream-egg mixture. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 35 minutes, until top is puffed and golden and knife inserted into center comes out clean. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes eight servings.

title: preacher's cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, bread crumbs and seasonings. Dip pork chops in batter.
Brown on both sides in oil in skillet. Place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, marshmallows, celery and nuts.
Add enough salad dressing to moisten.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Add more salad dressing, if needed.
Add optional ingredients if desired.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan in 425° oven until melted.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Coat chicken with mixture.
Place skin side down in pan and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake until thickest pieces are done; about 30 additional minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend salad oil and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add grated zucchini squash.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to first mixture and beat thoroughly. Pour into two greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: white bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl; toss well.
Serve at room temperature.
Yields 3 cups (serving size is 1 cup).

title: brown sugar pudding
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Add raisins and milk.
Mix well. Place in greased 8 x 10-inch pan. Dissolve brown sugar in hot water.
Add butter. Pour top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan heat salad oil.
Add onion; saute until tender (10 minutes).
Add potato, celery, garlic and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in broccoli, broth and basil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Into blender put 1/2 soup; cover and blend until smooth.
Repeat with remaining soup.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water (may use part pineapple juice) until skins burst.
Add sugar; cook 5 minutes.
Put gelatin in a bowl. Pour cranberries over; stir until it is dissolved.
Let cool, then add rest of ingredients.
Put in mold and chill.
You can freeze this after made.

title: coconut paste
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Let set for 2 hours before using to allow flavorings to blend.
Store in refrigerator in an airtight container.
Will store for several months.

title: pace setting enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic; drain.
Add Pace picante sauce, spinach, tomato sauce, tomatoes, bell peppers, lime juice and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Arrange 6 tortillas on bottom and up sides of lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, overlapping as necessary.
Top with half the meat mixture.
Arrange remaining tortillas, overlapping as necessary.
Spread sour cream over tortillas.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve.
Garnish with lettuce if desired and olives and serve with additional picante sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes and cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes well with cheese mixture.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place potatoes in a layer in pan.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour, turning once during baking.
When golden brown, sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into cubes (similar to potato salad). Cut bacon crosswise into thin strips.
Place bacon in frying pan and begin to brown.
Dice the onion and add to the bacon when it is almost done and saute until the onion is done.
When done, pour off the fat and place bacon and onions in a large (1-gallon) pot. Add the potatoes and just cover with water.
Add salt.
Cook on medium, stirring occasionally.
When the potatoes are done, add the creamed corn and add milk to fill.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Be sure to refrigerate the leftovers.
(It is better the second day.)

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Dice chicken and cook in pan; drain juice. In pot; combine cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, ro-tel and chicken stock. Cook on low to medium heat, stirring often. Layer chips in a 9 X 13 X 2 inch pan. Sprinkle

1/2 of onions over chips. Add 1/2 of the chicken (and half of mushrooms and olives, optional). Sprinkle cheese over chicken. Repeat with another layer of each. Pour soup mixture over all. Add cheese on top and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Simmer 20 minutes.
Add lemon and orange slices while simmering.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar until sugar is melted.
Cool and add oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: spaghetti fruit salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and cool. Cook eggs and sugar until thick. Add lemon juice, apples and pineapple. Fold in spaghetti. Let stand overnight or 12 hours. Add whipped topping and serve.

title: baked corn
directions: Bake at 350°.
Check oven to see when done, 35 minutes or more.

title: low calorie fruit dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into jar.
Cap the jar and shake vigorously.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake again just before serving.
Can be used as dressing for apples, pears and bananas because the citrus juice keeps them from turning brown.
Can also be used on green salad.
Contains 10 calories per serving. Serving equals 1 tablespoon.

title: dolmadesstuffed vine leaves
directions: Mix rice, mint, meat, tomatoes, onion and salt and pepper; place a small amount (about the size of a pecan) on each grape leaf and roll up.
(Keep in mind that rice will swell when cooked.)
Place in pan with 6 to 8 open leaves on top to prevent stuffed leaves from drying out.
Cover with water, oil and lemon juice.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 to 60 minutes.
Crock pots work well but take longer cooking time.
Stuffing can also be used for peppers and tomatoes.
Serve as hor's D'oeuvers or vegetable dish.
Goes good with a light lemon sauce.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer and add boiling water.
Batter will be thin.

title: orange chicken
directions: Mix all together and pour over chicken in a casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until juices run clear.
Serve over Uncle Ben's wild rice (prepared separately).

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until mixture is light and fluffy.
Place a vanilla wafer in the bottom of the baking cups, about 8.
Spoon cream cheese mixture evenly into cups.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
When cool, they can be topped with pie filling or pineapple.

title: zucchini carrot casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and carrots until tender; drain.
Saute onions in butter.
Add chicken soup, sour cream and 3/4 of the croutons.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients together until smooth. Place 1 package crescent dinner rolls in a 9 x 13 dish. Spread cream mixture on top. Place the other package of crescent dinner rolls on top of cream mixture. Beat egg white and spread on top. Sprinkle sugar on top of egg. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool!!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Break up sausage and brown.
Pour off drippings.
Place croutons in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over croutons.
Place sausage on top of cheese.
Beat eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk and mustard; pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Just before baking, combine soup and 1/2 cup milk. Pour over egg layer.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: artichoke bread
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic & sesame seeds, cook, stirring constantly, until lightly browned.
Remove from heat, stir in artichoke hearts and next three ingredients.

title: eye of round roast
directions: Preheat oven for 30 minutes at 500°.
Remove all fat from roast and rub with 1 tablespoon cooking oil.
Combine all ingredients and sprinkle on roast at room temperature.
Cook 5 minutes per pound and then turn off oven and leave for 2 hours.
Do not open oven door.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix ingredients with cucumbers.
Let come to a boil, stirring once in awhile.
Do not cook, just bring to a boil and can.

title: easy low-fat brownies
directions: Mix well and bake for 28 to 31 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, bacon, cheese and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over salad and stir just before serving.

title: chocolate chip strawberry pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add pudding
mix
and beat well.
Chill for
5	minutes.
Fold	in whipped cream.
Spoon 2 cups pudding into
3 quart glass bowl; top with half the vanilla wafers, half of the strawberries and half of chocolate chips.
Add remainder
of pudding and repeat layers. Garnish with chips, crushed
wafers and strawberries. Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil 4 to 6 quarts of water; add pasta and let cook for 8 to 10 minutes and drain noodles.
Then add the ingredients in the order listed.
Stir all together; may add more dressing if needed. Serves 8 to 10.

title: microwave dog yummies(for pets)
directions: Place the flour in bowl. Add the egg and enough broth to moisten flour.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Roll the dough into a ball.
Sprinkle flour on the work surface and break off small pieces of dough.
Form them into rolls or ring shapes. Place on large baking dish in single layer.
Bake on High in microwave for 10 minutes or until firm.
Let the biscuits cool and harden before giving to dog.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Melt shortening or margarine; add to warm milk.
Add gradually to mixture in bowl.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add flour.
Let rise until double in amount.
Punch down; roll out for rolls.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Saute onion and bacon.
Add the liquid off the green beans. Let this cook down to about 1/2 cup.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and green beans.
Heat thoroughly and serve.
Serves 4.

title: my mother's baked corn
directions: Beat sugar with egg yolks; beat whites separately.
Fold in after all other ingredients are mixed.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix all above ingredients, except beets.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Add beets and bring to a boil.
Serve warm.

title: shrimp spread(dip)
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise. Spread on a 12-inch serving platter (or whatever). Cover with seafood sauce. Sprinkle with cheese, shrimp, onions and tomato. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Butter a 9-inch pie plate or coat with cooking spray. Beat egg whites until foamy.

Add cream of tartar and beat until soft peaks begin to form. Gradually add the sugar, beating continuously. Add the vanilla and mix. Fold in the pecans and crackers. Spoon into prepared pie plate. Bake 20 minutes. Cool on a rack. When completely cooled, top with whipped cream or Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: giant taco dip
directions: Make in layers, starting with leaves or chunks of lettuce.
Mix refried beans and taco seasoning; spread on lettuce.
Combine avocado dip, green chillies and sour cream; spread gently for next layer.
Chop onions, tomatoes and black olives; spread over sour cream layer.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: horny toads
directions: In a double boiler, melt white chocolate (not almond bark) until smooth.
Stir in crushed peppermint sticks or discs.
Pour onto waxed paper and let set.
Break into bite size pieces and serve.
(I drop by teaspoonfuls and the pieces are automatically bite size.)

title: delicious doughnuts
directions: Heat shortening in an electric skillet or deep fryer.
Give each child a biscuit and have him poke a hole in the center of the biscuit with his finger.
Fry in shortening until golden brown. Drain.
Place sugar in a paper bag.
Add the fried doughnut and shake.
You can also add chocolate syrup and sprinkles. Whatever your taste desires.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and save the juice. Place pineapple in a square casserole dish. Mix flour, sugar and cheese and spread over the pineapple. Mix butter and crackers and spread over pineapple mixture. Pour the saved juice over this and bake at 350° until the topping is brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pot on top of stove.
Cook at low temperature for about 4 or 5 hours or until meat is stringy. Mash further with potato masher.
If too much liquid, strain. Serve on hard rolls.

title: baked rice pudding(makes 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Put all ingredients in a buttered baking dish and stir to blend.
Bake for 3 1/2 hours, stirring 3 times in the first hour of baking so the rice doesn't settle. Good served with whipped cream.

title: party mix
directions: Mix cereals in a large container, then spread out in shallow pan.
Melt oleo and add other ingredients.
Pour over cereals. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring often.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine hamburger, salt, pepper, onion and flour and fry; cook until red is gone. Add soup and stir until hot. Stir in mushrooms and carrots. Add sour cream.
Cooked noodles are next and the dish is ready for serving. Can be warmed in oven.

title: harvard beets
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in the reserved liquid, vinegar and butter.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add the beets; heat through.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and blend.
Make a paste of food coloring, vinegar and cocoa, then add to creamed mixture. Sift together remaining dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and blend thoroughly.
Pour into 3 greased, floured and paper lined cake pans.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes or until cakes are done.
Ice with special Red Velvet Icing.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy. Add oil and beat again.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Beat again while adding poppy seed.
Bake in an angel food cake pan, lightly greased, at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve warm or cool, with or without butter.

title: popcorn "cake"
directions: Melt margarine.
Add marshmallows and melt.
Add vanilla.
Mix other items together.
Grease Bundt pan.
Pour melted mixture, while hot, over other mixture.
Grease hands liberally to mix together and pack into pan.
Cool in refrigerator about 2 hours before turning out of pan.
(Dip bottom of filled pan into hot water to help release.)
Must use serrated knife to cut.
This is a finger-food snack.
Keep well wrapped so it doesn't become stale.

title: lisa baker's vegetable chili
directions: In large saucepot, saute zucchini, green pepper, onions, celery, carrots and garlic until tender-crisp.
Stir in tomatoes, picante sauce, water, bouillon and cumin.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes, stir occasionally.
Stir in olives and beans; simmer until heated.
Serve with cashews, cheese and sprouts.

title: sauerkraut rye bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine 1 cup of all-purpose flour, 1/4 cup rye flour, yeast, dry milk, sugar, caraway seed, salt and ginger; mix well.
In saucepan, heat water and oil until warm (120° to 130°).
Add to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually stir in sauerkraut, remaining rye flour and enough remaining all-purpose flour to make a firm dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Divide into 2 parts.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cooled cornbread in large bowl.
Add vegetables. Combine mayonnaise, dressing and mustard and toss lightly into cornbread mixture.
Chopped egg and cheese cubes may also be added.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat the sugar, powdered sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs; blend well. Stir in flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt; mix well. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours for easier handling.

title: hamburger pinwheels
directions: Saute onions in oil in saucepan for 5 minutes.
Measure 2 tablespoons onions and add to meat with other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.

title: bacon and horseradish dip
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: In small bowl, combine 4 ounce tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine eggs, onions, cracker crumbs, ground chuck, salt and pepper.
Add 4 ounces of tomato sauce and mix thoroughly.
Place mixture in a microwave ring mold. Spread tomato sauce mixture over top.
Cook, uncovered, on High 20 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy dinner
directions: Cube ham.
Cook potatoes until just done; don't overcook.
In large pan, layer potatoes, ham and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Save some cheese to put around the sides between the pan and potatoes. Cover with milk.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles and starts to brown.

title: salted peanut crunchie cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and blend in mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels and peanuts.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Makes about 12 dozen.

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill this, then serve.

title: curried turkey
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in greased baking dish. Place slices of turkey on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over turkey.
Sprinkle with cheese, bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ham cups
directions: Grease custard cups.

Fill 3/4 full and cook 25 minutes at 350°. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before turning out on top of warmed Chinese noodles. Put heated undiluted mushroom soup on top. Serve with fruit or congealed salad. Serves 7.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: *Zucchini or summer squash may be substituted for eggplant.

title: hoppin' john(will bring good luck if served on new year's eve.)
directions: Finely chop and cook in margarine the pepper and onion.
Cook until bubbly flour and milk.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese, peas, rice, ham and egg to milk mixture.
Turn into greased casserole. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in milk, soups and oleo.
Heat thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper.
Garnish with shredded cheese if desired.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Cream shortening, and sugar together.
Add beaten egg, 2 cups warm water, salt and yeast. Add flour.
Put dough in greased bowl and grease on top of dough. Cover and put in refrigerator.
When ready to use, take out as needed.
Let rise 3 hours.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Press mixture firmly on the bottom and on the sides to within 1-inch of the top of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Shred the lettuce and make a tossed salad with the celery, onion and radishes.
Just before serving, chop the corned beef and the eggs.
Add beef, eggs and cheese to the tossed salad.
Stir in enough Miracle Whip to make moist.

title: eclair
directions: Blend pudding and milk until thick.
Blend in Cool Whip. Layer 9 x 13-inch pan alternating
graham crackers with pudding. Cover with chocolate frosting, sprinkling graham crackers on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Place cabbage laves in a small amount of water over low heat for several minutes to soften.
Mix next 7 ingredients together. Place 1/4 cup of filling on each leaf.
Roll up and secure with a toothpick.
Place in casserole.
Pour soup over rolls and add a little water.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease 6-cup popover pan or 6 (6 ounce) custard cups generously.
Beat eggs slightly in medium bowl.
Beat in remaining ingredients just until smooth (do not overbeat).

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Cook onions in oleo.
Add eggs, sour cream and remaining ingredients.
