Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or 325° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top before baking.

title: kartoffel puffer(potato pancakes)
directions: Grate the raw potatoes very fine.
Add other ingredients to the potatoes.
Take small portions of dough and fry it in the pan like small pancakes.
We eat this with applesauce.

title: dottie's wedding punch
directions: Mix together.
Dredge with lime sherbet for a pretty float.

title: lazy-day pie
directions: Heat in pot the juice and fruit.
Pour in baking dish with 1 stick melted butter.
Mix flour, sugar, vanilla and milk to make thin batter; pour evenly over fruit.
Bake at 275° until brown or test with toothpick inserted to see if done.
Serve warm with ice cream, whipped topping or cream.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and 7 up.
Cook until mixture is thick.
Add Jello.
(Food coloring may be added, if desired.) Place strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour mixture over strawberries and let cool.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Start heating waffle iron. Stir together flour, baking powder and soda. Combine buttermilk and eggs.
Add milk-egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Beat with rotary beater just enough to moisten dry ingredients. Stir in salad oil. Bake.
Makes 8 waffles.

title: maple syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients, but flavoring, in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; turn heat down, cover and boil for 10 minutes.
Add maple flavoring.

title: lemon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour 3 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Remove seeds and chop jalapeno pepper.
Stir together all ingredients.
Place in a buttered 9x13-inch pan.

title: taco mac salad
directions: Cook spirals; drain.
Rinse well with cold water.
Brown meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning and mix well.
Cool.
In large bowl, mix rotini, green pepper, onion, cheese, tomatoes and lettuce. Chill.
Just before serving, stir in meat and French dressing. Toss.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop beef in food processor; place 1/2 of beef in bowl.
Add softened cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, Accent and onion. Blend well.
Shape into ball; coat with remaining beef.

title: caramel pie
directions: Combine flour with 1 1/4 cups sugar.
Beat egg yolks and gradually add milk.
Combine flour mixture and egg mixture.
Cook on medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Caramelize 3/4 cup sugar in iron skillet.
Add milk mixture to the caramelized sugar, stirring constantly in skillet.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Place in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all together until smooth.
Dip your favorite fruits.

title: tai cabbage
directions: Brown sausage with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain all grease. Cut up (sliver) cabbage over sausage and onion.
Steam until cabbage is slightly crunchy (10 minutes).
In separate skillet, scramble 6 eggs in small amount of margarine; salt and pepper. Place scrambled eggs over cabbage, sausage and onions and serve immediately with hot biscuits.

title: world's easiest cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Make batter of all dry ingredients.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir!
Pour fruit with juice evenly over other ingredients in pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven approximately 1 hour until golden brown.

title: yumesettia
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown meat and add soup and cream cheese.
Mix with noodles and corn.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour marinade over vegetable mixture and toss well. Chill at least 12 hours. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: cinnamon crispies
directions: Combine the hot water and vanilla in a small bowl; stir well. Combine the sugar and cinnamon; stir well.
Brush both sides of tortillas with margarine; brush each side with water mixture and sprinkle each side with sugar mixture.
Place on a wire rack in a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 1/2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 4.

title: orange-chocolate cake
directions: Spray a 10-inch tube pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick coating; dust with unsweetened cocoa powder.
Set aside. In large bowl, combine cake mix, yogurt, orange peel, orange juice, egg, egg whites, cooking oil, cinnamon and 1/2 cup water. Beat with an electric mixer on low speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes for tube pan and 35 to 40 minutes for sheet pan or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove cake from tube pan, if using; cool completely.
Drizzle icings over cake.
Makes 12 servings.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and drain excess fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, salt, seasoning and sugar.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. In a 9 x 13-inch casserole or lasagne pan, layer 1/3 of sauce, 1/2 of uncooked lasagne pieces, 1 cup cottage cheese and 1/3 of Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce and remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove foil and let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet and tangy carrots(salad)
directions: Combine carrots, green pepper and onion in a large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over vegetables. Chill thoroughly. Serve cold.

title: golden carrot souffle
directions: Cook carrots with 1/2 teaspoon salt in a small amount of water until tender; drain.
Combine carrots and oleo in blender and blend until smooth.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder and vanilla; blend well.
Spoon mixture into a greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add next 10 ingredients. Stir together good.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 4 dozen, maybe more.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Start with layer of cake in bottom of bowl, then add layers in this order:
1 layer pudding, 1 layer pineapple, 1 layer pie filling and 1 layer Cool Whip.

title: best-ever salad
directions: Dissolve jello, marshmallows and cream cheese in 2 cups boiling water.
Let stand until it begins to thicken.
(You have to work with the cream cheese a bit.)
Add balance of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Make into small balls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: rotel chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until cooked thoroughly.
Retain chicken broth. Boil spaghetti in chicken broth until tender.
Do not rinse. Saute onion and pepper in margarine.

title: honey-roasted nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line jellyroll pan with foil; grease foil.
In a small saucepan over medium heat, combine honey, butter or margarine and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; bring to boil.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Measure nuts into a medium bowl. Pour honey mixture over nuts; stir until evenly coated.
Spread on prepared pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, or until nuts are glazed and lightly browned.
Do not allow nuts to burn.
Cool in pan 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove foil.

title: sherbet-yogurt pie
directions: Warm marmalade in microwave; spread on pie shell.
Mix sherbet and yogurt together.
Put into pie shell, cover and freeze.
Take out of freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Garnish with fresh blueberries or fruit of choice.
Quick and easy to make ahead.

title: linguine with vegetables and provolone
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, bring salted water to a boil. Add pasta.
Cook 11 minutes.
Drain and return pasta to saucepan. Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic, green onions, zucchini and mushrooms.
Saute 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes. Add vegetables and cheese to pasta.
Gently sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into 2-inch pieces.
Put into saucepan and cover with water.
Cook until tender and then drain off the water.
Combine melted butter and parsley.
Pour over the potatoes and toss until well coated.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corned beef hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix nacho cheese soup and water.
Pour soup mix over beef and top with Tater Tots.
Bake until Tater Tots are brown.

title: jalapeno shrimp saute
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, melt butter.
When it foams, add the jalapenos and garlic.
Lower the heat and cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Add the shrimp and scallions; raise the heat to high and cook, tossing and stirring, until the shrimp turn a bright pink-orange and have curled, about 5 minutes.
With a slotted spoon, divide the shrimp among individual serving dishes.
Add the wine and Worcestershire sauce to the skillet; bring to a boil and cook, stirring, for 3 minutes. Stir in the salt and pour equal amounts of the sauce over the shrimp in each dish.
Serve at once.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Add onions, celery and green peppers to the crumbled corn bread.
Mix with the mayonnaise.
Top with bacon bits.
Chill and serve.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Add oil, water and food coloring.
Cook 3 minutes or until mix pulls away from sides of pan.
Knead slightly.
Almost immediately store in airtight container or Ziploc bag.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off grease.
Lay in a flat casserole dish.
Place frozen Tater Tots on top.
Top with cheese. Combine soup and milk.
Pour over top of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: low-fat chili
directions: In medium saucepan over medium-high heat, saute onion, garlic, green pepper, zucchini and water about 5 minutes or until soft. Brown turkey in skillet and drain off liquid.
Add to vegetables. Add tomato sauce, tomatoes with liquid, black beans and spices. Lower heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: christmas cutout cookies
directions: Melt butter; beat in eggs and add sugar.
Add flour.
Chill dough.
Roll out the dough and use cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 9 minutes.
Watch them!
The bottoms should be light brown and they do burn easily.
Decorate as desired.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Stir in cottage cheese and flour.
Add oregano, basil and garlic powder to the spaghetti sauce.
Stir in 1/2 cup of the spaghetti sauce into the sausage mixture.
Spoon about 1/3 cup meat mixture onto each tortilla; roll up jelly roll style.
Place tortillas, seam side down, in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour remaining spaghetti sauce over tortillas. Bake covered at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle Mozzarella cheese atop.
Bake 3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: tia's chili
directions: Brown ground beef in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Add onions and cook over high heat for 3-4 minutes.
Add tomatoes, juice and paste.
Bring to boil.
Let simmer gently for 20 minutes.
Add kidney beans, chili powder, Tabasco, garlic salt, pepper, crushed red chilis; simmer 20 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Make a syrup of 1 quart water (or tea) and sugar. Cool and if there is time before serving, allow the rind of 4 lemons to stand in the syrup for several hours. Add lemon juice and fruit. Add ice water or carbonated water or ginger ale just before serving. Serve in a punch bowl with ice cubes or a small block of ice (or with a quart brick of hard frozen lemon or mint sherbet) or in tall glasses filled at least 1/3 full of crushed ice and with slices of orange. Orange juice may be substituted for the pineapple (1 1/2 cups orange juice for 1 can pineapple). Makes 25 servings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Wash rice thoroughly and fry over medium heat in margarine. Add undiluted onion soup slowly, stirring after each addition. Add the mushrooms and
the liquid from the can.
Bake, covered, the first 50 minutes and uncovered the last 10 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Melt margarine.
Add garlic powder.
Stir and heat 3 minutes. Add catsup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Put chicken pieces in open pan.
Slice onions thinly. Salt and pepper chicken.
Put onion slices on top of chicken. Spoon sauce over onions.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is done.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add all ingredients to hamburger and simmer 1 hour. Makes 3 quarts.

title: skillet corned beef and cabbage
directions: Saute potatoes in oil in a large skillet, stirring often until tender and browned, about 10 minutes.
Add onion and saute for 1 minute more.
Add cabbage, corned beef, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Mix ingredients well.
Lower heat, cover skillet and cook for 12 to 15 minutes until hot and lightly browned on bottom.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and then remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 50 minutes at 300°.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare tube pan.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda and sugar.
Add cold coffee and Miracle Whip. Mix well.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oven-fried pork chops
directions: Coat chops according to package directions.
In paper towel lined oblong baking dish, arrange chops, ribs toward center.
Heat 15 to 16 1/2 minutes on power level 7, turning chops over once and rotating dish once.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon.
Crumble and toss 1/2 of bacon in large baking dish. Saute onion and green pepper until onion is lightly brown.
Add rice, tomatoes, salt and tomato sauce.
Mix together and put 1/2 of mixture in baking dish.
Crumble rest of bacon and put on first layer of rice mixture.
Then add rest of rice mixture.
Add grated cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients.
Mix together sour cream and powdered sugar.
Fold both mixtures together.
Freeze overnight and cut into squares.
You'll have a good salad.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on homemade pizza crusts.
Will cover 2 or 3 crusts.
Top with Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni, onions, etc.
Bake at 425° until cheese bubbles.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice and lemonade; chill.
Add ginger ale and ice a few minutes before serving.
Makes 40 to 50 punch cup servings.

title: taco cups
directions: Press biscuits on bottom and up sides of ungreased muffin tins.
Spoon meat mixture in first; top with chopped tomatoes, a dollop of sour cream and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 10 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Add butter.
Place in dish; spread cheese over broccoli and add soup. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Add onion rings and bake until browned.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Reserve broth from boiled chicken.
Combine 1/2 cup broth with cream of chicken soup.
Cut chicken in chunks and mix with thawed vegetables.
Place in casserole.
Pour soups over chicken and vegetable mixture.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo syrup, salt and raw peanuts.
Cook in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave for 4 more minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cook for 2 more minutes. Add soda and mix well.
Pour on a slightly greased cookie sheet. Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: basic instant frosting
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Beat until soft peaks form, 4 to 6 minutes.
Frosts 2 (8-inch) layers.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Saute celery and onion in melted butter.
Add this and sausage to the already cooked stuffing.
Toss lightly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and set aside.
Cut onions, pepper, celery and cook together.

Combine chicken with some of the stock with spaghetti, onion mixture, pimentos, olives and 2 kinds of soup. Place in buttered casserole dish (either an extra large one or two small ones) and place grated cheeses on top; push down to mix with top of other.
Bake 45 minutes or until cheeses brown.

title: barbecue kabob
directions: You will need wooden skewers.

title: polynesian turkey bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare rice mix according to package directions.
Transfer to a 3-quart oblong baking dish; set aside.

title: scallops a la nice
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Saute scallops until opaque. Drain olive oil.
Deglaze with wine and lemon juice.
Add tomatoes, Tabasco, butter and herbs.
Heat through.
Serve over angel hair pasta.
Serves 4.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a slow cooker. Cover and cook on high one hour. Then turn to low and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Serve hot.

title: diane's waffles
directions: Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in waffle iron.

title: freeda midkiff's clam chowder
directions: Place salt pork or bacon and onion in a pan and cook until onion is a golden brown.
Add 2 cups of water (clam liquid and enough water to make 2 cups) and potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Melt butter; stir in flour, milk and seasonings. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Combine mixture; add clams. Heat; do not boil.
Add broken crackers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sicilian-style steak
directions: Soak garlic in oil for 1 hour or longer.
Preheat grill or broiler.
Combine bread crumbs with salt, pepper, oregano and cheese.
Pat steak dry with paper towels.
Stir garlic-oil mixture well.
Dip steak into garlic mixture.
Roll in seasoned bread crumbs.
Grill or broil to desired degree of doneness.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown rump roast in small amount of oil.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Can be cooked on top of stove, covered, on very low heat or in 325° oven until tender.

title: chicken caroline
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in casserole dish.
Place chicken on the melted butter; add salt and pepper.
Cut onion into slices and place on chicken.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top of sliced onion.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Dissolve sugar in cream.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Blend well in blender.
Put in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: farmers breakfast
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes for 30 minutes.
Rinse under cold water.
Slice potatoes.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Combine and refrigerate.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese and pineapple together.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Roll into ball.

title: chocolate nut squares
directions: Microwave 3/4 cup butter and 2 ounces chocolate squares on High for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add sugar and let cool.
Add eggs one at a time until well blended.
Stir in rest.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: cranberry and strawberry salad
directions: Put strawberries in last and refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Blend well.
Turn into buttered medium deep baking dish.
Add topping.

title: 6 weeks muffins
directions: Cream the Crisco oil, sugar and eggs.
Add the buttermilk, flour, soda and salt.
Mix ingredients together.
Add Raisin Bran last.
Fill tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Will keep for 6 weeks.

title: dump cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Grease and flour.
Into cake pan, dump and spread cherry pie filling and pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix, coconut and pecans.
Pour melted oleo over the whole cake.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Cream jello and cream cheese together until well mixed. Add boiling
water
and
stir until all jello mixture is dissolved. Add pecans and pineapple and blend in.
Add cold milk and stir. Place in refrigerator until set.

title: bean and onion casserole
directions: Cook beans about 10 minutes with dash of salt; drain.
Add margarine.
Place layer of beans in casserole; add layer of soup and layer of onions.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: pina colada dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate. Serve with fruit.

title: sunday layered salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer all ingredients in order given.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Do not toss. Cut into squares to serve.
Will keep several days.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: can't pass'em by cookies
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter together in double boiler. Then add other ingredients.
Drop from spoon onto wax paper and let harden.

title: overnight refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs, 4 cups flour and salt.
Stir, then beat until smooth, about 1 minute. Stir in remaining flour (you may want to use your hands to work in last 2 cups).
This will be a soft dough.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator overnight or until needed.

title: big batch cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine cake mix, yeast, 1 cup flour and salt in a large bowl. Stir in water, eggs and oil.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer 2 minutes.
Gradually add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a well-floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Cover dough and let rest 10 minutes.

title: italian zucchini bake
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in sour cream, bread crumbs and oregano.
Cover bottom of 10 x 6-inch baking dish with 2 cups zucchini sliced.
Top with meat mixture and cheese.
Arrange the rest of zucchini slices around edge of pan, cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and salt.
Cut oleo into mixture with pastry blender until crumbly.
Heat milk until scalded; add 2 eggs, slightly beaten, and yeast mixture.
Combine all three with flour and stir with a spoon until mixed well.
Refrigerate overnight. Divide dough into two parts.
Roll into a circle (use flour on board to keep from sticking).
Cut circle into 12 crusts (like a pie).
Starting at wide end, roll up and shape like a crescent. Place on a greased baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter and let rise (about an hour).
Bake at 400° 8 to 10 minutes.
Brush with melted butter (or oleo) after you take them out of oven.
Yields 2 dozen rolls.

title: warm cranberry punch
directions: Mix in crock-pot and heat on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: chicken cilantro
directions: Wash and remove skin from chicken.
Place butter and garlic in frying pan, place over medium heat.
While the mixture is melting, cut up chicken and place in the pan. Cook chicken until white and stir so it does not stick.
This should take about 5 minutes. At the 4 minute mark, add salt, fresh cilantro and lemon juice.
Stir.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Combine instant coffee with 1 cup boiling water.
Set aside to cool slightly.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in slow oven for 45 minutes.
Very old recipe.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Cream the cream cheese. Slowly blend in 2 cups of confectioners sugar. Mix in chocolate. Add vanilla, salt and nuts. Press into a well greased pan and place in refrigerator until firm, around 15 minutes. Cut in squares.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients.
Mix next 3 ingredients together. Pour marshmallow mix over popcorn and press into a greased 10-inch angel food cake pan.
Cool in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Loosen and remove from pan. Cut with serrated knife.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Beat together whole egg and yolks until foamy.
Mix sugar, salt and flour in top of double boiler.
Add egg yolks, lemon rind, lemon juice and milk.
Cook about 10 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Pour mixture in baked pastry; beat egg whites and bake meringue until light brown.

title: spiced green beans
directions: Pour mixture over beans and onion.
Let stand overnight.

title: sour cream frosting
directions: Mix all together.
Cook slowly, stirring often until thick. Spread between layers or on top of cake.

title: green beans napoli
directions: To prepare topping, melt butter in small frying pan; add crumbs and stir over moderate heat until crumbs are golden in color.
Blend in paprika, remove from heat.
Add Parmesan cheese and toss until blended.
Heat green beans, drain off any liquid from canned beans.
Add oil and garlic salt to beans.
Toss lightly.
Serve topped with crunch mixture.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Blend cream of celery soup with 3/4 cup water.
Measure out 1/4 cup soup mixture.
Combine with ground beef, bread crumbs, minced onions, parsley flakes and one slightly beaten egg.
Add salt and pepper.
Shape into meat balls about 1-1/2-inches in diameter. Brown in 1 tablespoon shortening in a large skillet.
Add remaining soup mixture.
Cover and cook over low heat a few minutes; stir occasionally (approximately 10 minutes).
Can be served over rice, biscuits or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: lime pickles
directions: Mix cold.
Put pickles in mixture and set overnight.
Next day, heat mixture and boil about 35 minutes.
Seal.

title: baked beans with ground beef
directions: Brown beef and onions in skillet; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in uncovered pan or dish at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; place in crock-pot first thing in the morning.
Add celery, Tabasco sauce and corn. Cook on low for 6 to 7 hours.
When chicken is done, transfer to Dutch oven.
Add lima beans and tomatoes.
Cook on medium heat about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Fry bacon until crisp; crumble and sprinkle over casserole just before serving.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Sift together in large bowl the flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt; mix well.
Add lard, sour milk, egg, vanilla and boiling coffee; mix well.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: tuna salad sandwiches
directions: Drain tuna.
Place in a bowl. Flake with fork. Add eggs, salad cubes and enough mayonnaise to make mixture spreadable.
Mix well. Spread tuna salad on half the bread slices. Top
with remaining bread slices. Trim crusts from sandwiches. Cut each sandwich into 4 squares.
Serve sandwiches with favorite potato or corn chips. Yields 6 to 7 servings.

title: grilled asparagus
directions: Marinate asparagus in next 5 ingredients for 30 minutes. Grill for 5 minutes each side.

title: lemon cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool.
Mix cake mix, eggs and oil.
Add jello mixture and beat at moderate speed for 3 minutes. Bake in 8 x 13-inch pan at 325° for Pyrex or 350° for aluminum foil for 30 minutes.
While baking, mix powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Pierce cake top with fork and pour mixture over it. Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into bite-size balls. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine macaroni and water in 9 inch microproof baking dish. Double-wrap tightly with plastic wrap and cook on HI for 9-10 minutes or until macaroni is cooked but still is firm.
Pour off any remaining water.
Stir in cheese, butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on HI for 6 minutes.
Stirring once.
4 servings.
Total cooking time: 15-16 minutes.

title: fruited cheese salad
directions: In bowl, blend together cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in dry Jell-O; fold in pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Press into a 7 or 8 cup mold.
Chill for several hours.

title: burger-mushroom bake
directions: Combine 1/4 cup soup with all the ingredients except water; mix thoroughly.
Shape into 6 patties.
Place in shallow baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Combine remaining soup and water.
Pour over meat and bake 10 minutes. This is excellent served over rice.
Serves 6.

title: vegie pizza
directions: Stir-fry chicken and vegies.
Put on pie crust and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and pie crust is warm, about 15 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix well and mold into 5 to 6 patties.
Put in casserole. Cover with Sauce.

title: sour cream pound cake(good!)
directions: Grease and flour Bundt (tube) pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In one big mixing bowl, put sifted flour, then resift with soda.
In another large mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar until smooth and fluffy.

title: easy brownies
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil, then add this hot mixture to the flour and sugar.
Add the beaten eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Add nuts.
Bake in an 11 x 15-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into churn; finish filling with milk.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until slightly tender; drain.
In casserole dish, alternate squash and cheese.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden and squash is bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
Add cold water; mix well.
Pour into serving bowl.
Chill until partially set. Stir in carrots, pineapple and cheese.
Chill until set.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pearl's refrigerated pickles
directions: Mix the salt, vinegar, sugar and celery salt; pour over the cucumbers,
onions and green peppers.
Stir and let sit an hour or so.
Put in jars and refrigerate.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg yolks and milk, then add to dry ingredients.
Mix well at high speed.
Stir in slightly cooled butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter, leaving little tufts showing.
Bake until steam stops. Flip to cook other side.
These are light pancakes.
Delicious.

title: microwave zucchini parmesan
directions: Set power select
at High.
In 8-inch round baking dish combine zucchini,
Parmesan
cheese
and
tomato sauce.
Heat, covered,
8 to 9 minutes or until zucchini is tender, stirring once.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: lo-cal-nonfat banana pudding
directions: Blend.
Line dish with vanilla wafers and top with 4 or 5 sliced ripe bananas.
Pour pudding on top and chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: frozen strawberry jam
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar and set aside.
Put Sure-Jell and water in pan and stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Add to strawberries and sugar and mix well until thick. Put in containers and freeze.

title: tomato zucchini casserole
directions: Rub casserole with butter.
Line dish with a layer of zucchini, onion and sliced tomatoes; top layer with 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon basil and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Dot with butter. Repeat layers; top with remaining salt, basil and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, oil, pumpkin and eggs; beat until blended. Sift dry ingredients, add and mix well.
Stir in water.
Spoon into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or three 7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pans.
Sprinkle top with a mixture of 1/4 cup white sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, if desired.

title: suzy's punch
directions: Mix and serve cold.
Requested by students.

title: miraculous salad
directions: Mix together in your finest cut-glass fruit bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Just before serving, add the strawberries and bananas.

title: no-sugar date nut bread
directions: Mix and bake in cast-iron skillets at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Makes two 10-inch skillets.

title: pretzels
directions: Melt oleo in13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix with onion soup.
Add pretzel pieces and stir.
Bake 1 hour at 250°; stir frequently. Cool and eat.

title: homestyle stew
directions: Combine flour, salt, thyme and pepper.
Coat meat cubes with flour mixture.
In large saucepan, brown meat, half at a time, in hot Crisco.
Sprinkle any remaining flour mixture over meat during browning.
Return all meat to saucepan.
Stir in the cider, water and vinegar.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until meat is tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions and celery.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes more.
Skim off excess fat.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tea cakes #2
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Drop on a cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: tomato french dressing
directions: In covered jar, combine all ingredients; chill.
Shake well before serving.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: pork roast
directions: Trim fat from roast.
Place in pan and pierce with a long fork.

title: dump cake
directions: Oil pan and add ingredients in layers.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Do not drain pineapple.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Top with Quick Fudge Frosting.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Beat egg yolks in small bowl with electric mixer on high speed until thick and lemon colored, about 3 minutes. Gradually add sugar and beat on high speed. Heat 1 cup whipping cream in 2-qt. saucepan over medium heat just until hot (do not boil). Gradually stir half of the hot cream into egg yolk mixture; stir back into hot cream in saucepan. Cook over low heat about 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens (do not boil). Let cool for about 10 minutes. Add chocolate to egg yolk mixture and stir until mixture thickens and chocolate is well blended, about 5 minutes. Cover and refrigerate for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally, just until chilled. Beat 1 1/2 c. whipping cream in chilled medium bowl with electric mixer on high speed until stiff. Mix 3/4 c. of whipped cream into chocolate mixture until blended. Fold remaining whipped cream gradually into chocolate mixture until well blended. Pipe or spoon mixture into cups or small dessert bowls. Refrigerate any remaining dessert.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, white syrup, oatmeal, vanilla and coconut. Add pecans, if desired.
Mix well and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for about 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Break
salmon apart with fork;	remove	any
bones
and skin. Add egg, onion, pepper, milk
and
water
and mix well. Add bread crumbs and mix.
Place
mixture in greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Serves 4.

title: crescent chicken rolls
directions: Mix soup, cheese, milk and stock.
Pour half of this into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Separate rolls and place as much chicken as you can in each roll. Roll, tucking edges in.
Place rolls in mixture. Pour remaining mixture over rolls.
Put remaining chicken around in the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: frosting
directions: Beat with mixer until thick, 5 to 10 minutes on medium speed.

title: fudgy christmas wreath
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, cook and stir milk and chocolate chips until chocolate melts and mixture is slightly thickened, about 6 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in nuts and vanilla. Cool until it starts to set, about 15 minutes. Line a baking sheet with waxed paper. Spoon chocolate mixture by 2 tablespoonfuls into small mounds to form a wreath. Decorate with cherries. Chill until firm. Serve chilled. Yield: about 24 servings.

title: curried spice fruit
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and dissolve.
Sprinkle in curry powder.
Combine with fruit and place in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place cream, butter, garlic and nutmeg in pan.
Simmer on low heat about 10 minutes until cream reduced to 2 cups and thickens slightly.
Butter casserole and arrange 1/3 potatoes in dish.
Add 1/3 combination cheeses.
Season with salt, 3 layers up.
Dot with butter; add cream to cover casserole.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: jerky
directions: Cut meat with grain in 1/2-inch strips.
Mix other ingredients to make marinade.
Submerge meat in marinade for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Place meat strips on oven rack in oven and cook for 8 hours at 150°.
Use foil to catch the drippings.
Store in airtight containers.
Will keep a year.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute celery, pepper and pimento in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until hot.
Serve over rice.

title: hot dog chili
directions: With a very sharp knife, cut beef across grain into thin strips, 1/8-inch thick.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger; add beef.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.

title: rich white bread
directions: Scald milk, sugar, salt and margarine.
Dissolve yeast.
Add yeast, eggs, and 2 3/4 cups flour; beat with spoon.
Add flour, a little bit a a time.
Turn onto lightly floured board and let rest 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes. Roll into ball.
Put in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rise again.
Turn onto board and shape into loaves.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: cinnamon logs
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Sift flour and cinnamon together and add to butter mixture. Add egg yolk. Mix well and spread mixture on a greased cookie sheet, 10 x 15-inch. Brush top with beaten egg white. Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake in 350° oven until slightly brown, approximately 15 minutes. Remove from oven and cut into bars. Makes 4 dozen 1 x 3-inch logs.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 8 servings.

title: russian corn bread
directions: Mix 1/2 the cheese and all the other ingredients together. Put remaining cheese on top of batter and bake for 1 hour at 350°. You should use an iron skillet for this recipe.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil in large kettle until tender. Discard garlic; add tomatoes, tomato paste, parsley, salt, pepper, oregano, basil and bay leaves.
Bring to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, stirring occasionally for 2 hours.
Add mushrooms and wine and cook, uncovered, 30 minutes longer (optional).
Cool and freeze.
I use Ziploc bags.

title: caramel filling
directions: Put all ingredients into a pan; let boil hard for 2 minutes by the clock. Add pinch of soda. Remove from fire and beat until cold. Nuts may be added.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Cut in soft butter until fine crumbs result. Add seeds and raisins. Mix.
Add milk.

title: fruit punch for a crowd
directions: *Made by pouring 2 quarts boiling water over 5 tablespoons tea.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: nelda's hawaiian bread sandwich
directions: Thaw spinach.
Squeeze out all excess water.
Add to soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise and onion.
Put this mixture in fridge to cool and blend.
Cut bread crossways three times.
Fill each layer and stack like a cake.
Refrigerate.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain off grease.
Then add tomato sauce, taco seasoning, taco sauce, mustard and onion to hamburger and simmer 20 minutes.
Crush Doritos in bag.
In a casserole dish, layer first meat mixture, then cheese, then Doritos.
Do this until you are out of the meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake long enough to melt cheese thoroughly.

title: potato casserole
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Mix well.
Add ginger ale and serve over ice.

title: rhubarb dump cake
directions: Heat pineapple until boiling.
Add cornstarch and water, cooking until thickened.
Add sugar and gelatin; set aside. Butter a 3-quart baking dish.
Line with rhubarb.
Pour pineapple sauce over rhubarb.
Pour dry cake mix over fruit and pat down. Cut oleo in small pieces.
Spread over cake mix.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: chicken deluxe
directions: Chicken should be split, skinned and boneless.
Arrange chicken in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top with American cheese.
Combine soup and water.
Spoon sauce over chicken and cheese.
Crush herb seasoning and sprinkle over chicken.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until breasts are soft when pierced with fork.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup (undiluted).
Add cream cheese and heat until dissolved.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water and add to warm mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill overnight.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: easy fudge brownies
directions: In a large bowl, stir all of the ingredients until just moistened.
Spray a 9 1/2 x 13-inch glass casserole dish with a nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool about 10 minutes and spread with fudge topping.

title: mama ethel's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine tomato sauce, chili powder, vinegar, onions, garlic powder, oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Roll lemons to soften.
Slice lemons and squeeze juice into mixture.
Stir well.
Add lemon rinds.
Stir and simmer (uncovered) for 30 minutes.
(One-half teaspoon of ground cayenne pepper may be added for a spicier sauce.)

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain well. Meanwhile, combine whipping cream and remaining 4 ingredients. Pour cream mixture over hot pasta immediately after draining pasta and toss gently.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: chili and velveeta dip
directions: Stir Velveeta and chili over low heat until melted.
Serve with tortilla chips or cut up vegetables.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve in round loaf of bread that has been hollowed out to form bowl.
Delicious with bread cubes, vegetables, chips, etc.

title: cinnamon monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 3/4 cup of sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons of cinnamon in plastic bowl with lid.
Seal with top and shake to mix.
Cut biscuits into quarters and add to sugar mixture.
Seal bowl and shake until biscuits are coated.
Grease Bundt pan and layer biscuits in pan.
Add 1 cup of sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons of cinnamon to melted butter; heat until boiling. Drizzle over biscuits.
Bake about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Cook about 1 minute.
With a whisk, blend in flour, bouillon and pepper.
Add milk gradually. Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat; add 2 cups grated cheese.
Stir to melt.
This can be made while macaroni is cooking or made before.
Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Pour into a colander to drain.
Do not rinse.
Immediately layer macaroni, cheese and sauce in a large deep casserole or pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
End with layer of cheese on top.
Bake in moderate oven until bubbly or slightly brown.
Remove and sprinkle with paprika.
For small size use 1/2 of all ingredients.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain and stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of meat, chips and cheese in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes or until well heated.
Top with lettuce, chopped tomatoes and sliced olives.

title: pineapple cheese mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into a 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm. Serves 8.

title: gene's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour in square pan of metal or glass.
Cook in 350° to 400° oven until brown.

title: sodsuppe(sweet soup)
directions: Cook raisins, prunes and large tapioca until well cooked and in a little more water than you would ordinarily use.
Then add any combination of canned fruit and juice you like such as apricots, raspberries, sweet cherries or strawberries (fresh or frozen are good).
After bringing to a boil again, add a few thin slices of lemon.
Boil for 1 to 2 minutes.
May be eaten warm or cold, as a dessert or excellent for persons who are ill and haven't much appetite.

title: maine molasses pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together and turn into an unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in a hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to moderate (350°) and bake 30 minutes longer, or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Makes 1 one-crust (9-inch) pie.

title: easy lemon cookies
directions: Mix together cake mix, Cool Whip and egg.
Refrigerate before rolling.
Roll in 10x powdered sugar before cooking.
Put small balls on
a cookie sheet; bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
(They need to look a little undercooked when you take them out.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut dried beef into small bits.
Add rest of ingredients and beat well.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: amish pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients, then water, stirring just until mixed.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: hot seafood dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Mix in remaining ingredients. Serve warm with dry toast. Salt to taste.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Boil together brown sugar, butter and cream.
Then add powdered sugar to consistency to spread. Can add peanut butter if desired.

title: walnut-coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with the buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add chopped walnuts and coconut, blending well.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool completely and frost with cream cheese frosting and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook potatoes and celery in water until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain; reserve liquid and set veggies aside.

title: bishop's cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package, except bake only 20 minutes in a cookie sheet pan (10 x 15 x 1-inch).
Beat pudding as directed.
Add cream cheese while beating.
Beat until stiff and spread on cooled cake.
Spread layers as follows:
Coconut, pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate at least one hour before serving.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: sweet and fluffy
directions: Mix first two ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into dish or dishes.
Freeze.
Set out 1 to 2 hours before serving. Mmm!

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Put fryer pieces into large pan or Dutch oven, pour Coke over the chicken parts and slowly cook for 1 hour.
Pour off excess Coke and add barbecue sauce.
Simmer about 20 to 30 minutes in sauce. Serve.

title: ground turkey soup(no cholesterol)
directions: Brown turkey and drain.
Add water and rest of the ingredients. Bring to boil, then simmer 1 hour or until done.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown and drain meat.
Stir in salsa, corn, Miracle Whip and chili powder.
Layer in 2-quart casserole. Bake 20 minutes.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes, if desired.

title: crisco single pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Add water. Mix well.

title: mexican rice and fried plantains
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat 1/4 cup oil over medium heat.
Add rice; stir to coat.
Saute rice until pale golden, about 10 minutes. Spoon off and reserve oil.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water until soft.
Cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add 7 tablespoons of liquid from raisins and the soda.
Beat in eggs.
Add cooked, drained raisins.
Stir in oatmeal, flour, cinnamon, salt and vanilla.
Add nuts last.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Store in tight container.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix well and put in a 10 x 10-inch pan or dish.
Spread thin layer of salsa over mixture.
Top with chopped lettuce, tomatoes, grated Monterey Jack cheese and black olives (optional).
Chill for several hours and serve with tortilla chips.
Best if eaten the day it is prepared.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello and cream cheese really well.
Add water and pineapple.
Chill until beginning to set, then fold in Cool Whip and chill completely.

title: slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onion and green pepper. On this, put 3/4 cup sugar.
In a saucepan, bring to boil the Wesson oil, vinegar, 1 tablespoon sugar, dry mustard, salt and celery seed.
Pour hot mixture over cabbage mixture. Cover and keep in refrigerator.

title: chocolate rugalach
directions: In medium bowl, cream 1 cup butter with cream cheese.
Add flour and salt; blend until dough begins to hold together.
Gather into bowl, transfer to floured surface and knead until smooth. Divide into 6 parts, wrap each in plastic wrap and chill.

title: nearly instant strawberry trifle
directions: Place cake in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart trifle bowl or other glass bowl.
Pour orange juice over; set aside.
In blender or food processor, puree 1 pint of the strawberries with 4 tablespoons of the sugar; pour over cake.
Slice remaining strawberries; arrange over cake and set aside.

title: potato tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and put in baking dish.
Mix both cans of soup with 1/2 can water; bring to boil and pour over ground beef. Spread cheese over this; layer with potato tots.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle some paprika on top for color.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peach ice cream
directions: In heavy saucepan, heat milk over low until hot but not boiling.
Stir in sugar and salt until dissolved.
Gradually stir a quarter of the hot mixture into eggs, mixing constantly.
Return all to the saucepan, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook and stir for 10 to 12 minutes or until mixture coats the back of a metal spoon.
Remove from the heat; cool.
Chill for at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir well.
Let shortening dissolve.
Sprinkle yeast in warm water; let stand about 5 to 10 minutes, then add to first mixture.
Put well beaten egg into mixture.
Add mixture to flour; mix well, etc.
Let rise, as desired, and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown. Makes 2 dozen.

title: grandpa's salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake well.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and shortening.
Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1/2 cup to sprinkle over batter.
To remaining crumbs, add baking powder, soda and spice.
Mix. Add milk and eggs.
Mix. Pour in pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Nuts and cinnamon may be sprinkled over crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: potato salad
directions: In dish, layer potatoes.
Layer dressing.
Layer potatoes. Layer dressing, ending with dressing.
Serve cold.

title: persimmon brownies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter together. Add persimmons, buttermilk and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into a 10 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool and add Cream Cheese Icing.

title: sausage and potato soup
directions: Brown sausage and onion. Put in soup pot. Add hash browns, water and chicken broth. Bring to a boil. Simmer for 3 minutes. Add milk and soups. Makes 11 cups.

title: mrs. claus' fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage (236°), stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add chocolate bits, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nut meats.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Immediately score in squares and top each piece with nut half.
Cool and cut in squares.
Makes 3 dozen 1 1/2-inch pieces.

title: eight-vegetable marinated salad
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl and toss lightly.
Combine vinegar, sugar and oil in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour hot marinade over vegetables; stir gently.
Cover and chill salad overnight.
Serves 12.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix.
The longer it stands, the better it gets.

title: marinated avocados and tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes and arrange on a plate.
Peel and slice avocados and arrange on top of tomatoes.
Pour Italian dressing (oil and vinegar type) over tomatoes and avocados.
Season with pepper and salt.
Chill 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.

title: pineapple right side up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, margarine and crushed pineapple with juice and juice from the tidbits.
Pour batter into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle tidbits on top and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the sugar, oil and eggs well.
Sift the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Add the apples and pecans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in an oblong pan.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Arrange chicken over rice.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours or until chicken and rice are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Press cookie dough onto cookie sheet and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Blend flour, cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth, spread on cooled cookie dough.
Peel, core and slice apples (dipped in lemon juice). Arrange over dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Heat caramel and drizzle over apples and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: pistachio inside outside cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all cake ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan for 40 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool on rack.
Split into 3 layers and frost.

title: fast mexican chili
directions: In skillet, cook together until beef is done.
Hot peppers can be used instead of chili powder for hotter chili.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Mix vanilla pudding, milk, cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Make alternating layers with the mixture:
Oreo cookies, pudding mixture and cream cheese mixture. Top with Cool Whip.

title: perfect pie crust everytime
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in a large bowl with fork.
Add shortening and stir until crumbly.

In small bowl, beat water, vinegar and egg. Combine the two mixtures, stirring with fork until all ingredients are moistened. Divide dough in 5 portions and with hands, shape each into flat round patty. Wrap in plastic wrap or waxed paper and chill at least 1/2 hour (or freeze).

title: zippy seafood dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: dump salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges; cut orange slices in half.
Dump all ingredients in large bowl and mix by hand until very well blended.

title: vegetable with beef stew
directions: Bring beef broth to a boil in small saucepan; cook 15 minutes or until reduced to 2 cups.
Set aside.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened (batter should be lumpy).
Lightly grease muffin cups or line with paper bake cups; fill 2/3 full.
Bake about 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pans; serve warm.

title: cherry pudding(no cholesterol)
directions: Place cherries in an 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Mix dry ingredients
and
add milk.
Pour over cherries.
Bake at 350° until cake rises to top and is brown.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on. Boil until tender.
Peel and grate.
Salt to taste. Cook margarine and cheese together in a large pan until melted. Add sour cream. Stir well.
Stir in potatoes until well mixed.
Pour into buttered casserole. Dot with butter. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: indoor camper's delight
directions: For each camper's delight, place half a candy bar and a giant marshmallow on half a graham cracker.
Place on paper towel and microwave on High 10 to 15 seconds or until marshmallow is softened.
Top with other half of graham cracker.
Give a little squeeze and enjoy!

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add to jello.
Fold in pineapple and 7-up.
Put in bowl and chill.

title: chicken taquitos
directions: Simmer chicken in water for 20 minutes.
Remove and cool. Shred.
Saute green onions and garlic in oil slightly.
Stir in chicken, tomatoes, broth, flour, cumin, oregano, chili powder and salt.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Note:
Use 13 x 8 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: In bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla gradually. Add whipping cream and milk.
Put into ice cream freezer.
Crank 20 to 30 minutes.
Use salt and ice as needed to freeze.

title: chicken almindzini
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour and seasonings.
Gradually add milk; cook over low heat stirring constantly until thickened.
Add cheese and wine.
Stir until cheese is melted.
In large bowl, combine mayonnaise mixture, spaghetti, chicken, broccoli, 3/4 cup nuts, mushrooms and pimento; toss lightly.
Pour mixture into 11 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Drain pineapple juice into 2-quart glass casserole.
Stir in cornstarch, brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook in microwave oven on High for 4 minutes, or until mixture boils.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Stir in green pepper and pineapple.
Cook in microwave oven, covered, on High for about 6 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Place sausage in larger dish and pour sauce over it.
Sauce may also be used over meatballs, cocktail franks or vegetables.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add onion and saute.
Add soy sauce and gravy sauce with water and celery.
Stir and simmer until tender.
Add drained bean sprouts and cook 5 minutes.
Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: homemade banana graham cracker pudding
directions: Put a
layer of graham crackers in a 1 1/2-quart casserole
or baking dish.
Slice bananas evenly over graham crackers.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir and mix well.
Add cornflakes.
Stir until flakes are well coated.
Drop by tsp. onto wax paper.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Beat eggs without separating.
Add milk and other ingredients. Pour in oiled pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Stir butter in with cooked spaghetti.
Add Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form into crust and spread in buttered 10-inch pie plate.

title: tomato-vegetable noodle soup
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine soup and water.
Add vegetables and noodles.
Over medium heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: mostaccioli vegetable salad
directions: Gradually add mostaccioli and 1 tablespoon salt to rapidly boiling water so that water continues to boil.
Cook, covered, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Drain again.

title: baked catfish
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish, well. Combine breadcrumbs, cheese, herbs, and seasonings. Dip catfish in melted margarine and roll in crumb mixture. Arrange fish into a baking dish. Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily. Garnish with lemon wedges.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix well and chill until ready to serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage lasagna wraps
directions: Cook and drain lasagna noodles.
Split the sausages lengthwise and stuff each with 1/2 slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Wrap each sausage with a lasagna cooked noodle.
Place in a baking dish and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: gumdrop fruit cake
directions: Mix sugars, Crisco and butter well.
Add eggs and beat well. Add applesauce and sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts, raisins, gumdrops and place in bread tins.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, raisins, salt and spices in water and cook on top of stove until it boils. Boil for 5 minutes. Cool. Dissolve the baking soda in water and add. Mix in the flour and beat well. Add nuts. Bake in moderate oven for 35 minutes in a square pan. Cover with a simple white frosting or dribble on a glaze. Good plain or served with vanilla ice cream.

title: fire department potatoes
directions: Peel, wash and quarter potatoes.
Place in pot; cover with water.
Pour sauce over and bring to a rolling boil.
Cook until done, approximately 45 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all but chips and refrigerate several hours.
Toss with chips or serve chips alongside as a dip too.
Serves several.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar with butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in bananas and lemon juice.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in anything optional.
Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350°
for about 1 hour or until done when tested.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Drain fat of meat, then add all of ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: colorful meat loaf
directions: Mix meat loaf mix with bread crumbs, salt, pepper, basil, parsley, cheese and water.
Blend well.
Spread this mix on wax paper (rectangle).
Spread mashed potatoes on top of meat mix. Then spread spinach on top of potatoes.
Roll up like a jelly roll, removing wax paper.
Bake in an oblong pan at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.	Roll
into balls and press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat with milk until creamy enough to spread over bread. Take 4 x 4 slices of bread and spread each with cheese, chicken and ham, 4 times each. Stack each one. Make 4 stacks. Spread cream cheese over all of the stacks. Ice this like a cake.

title: oatmeal pie(mock pecan)
directions: Stir together the ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in a 350° oven until brown and firm, about 45 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat butter in rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven until melted.
Mix flour, paprika, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Coat chicken; put skin side down in pan.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over and bake 30 minutes longer or until juices run clear.
Makes 6 servings.

title: best lasagna
directions: Boil noodles as directed.
Brown ground meat and sausage, crumbled.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Drain well.
Place cooked noodles in large baking pan.
Spread cottage cheese over noodles.
Spread meat and sauteed seasonings over cottage cheese.
Pour Ragu and sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake at 300° until hot and bubbly.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, chopped onion, soup and 1 cup cheese together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, milk and peanuts in a 250° electric skillet.
Cook to soft ball stage (240°).
Remove (turn off) from heat.
Add vanilla, butter and food coloring.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken (this process can take approximately 20 to 30 minutes).
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper or foil.
Let stand until firm.

title: fresh peach pies
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, water and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Mix cream cheese and remaining 1/2 cup sugar in bowl.
Spread cream cheese mixture in bottom of pie shells.
Arrange peach slices over top.
Spoon gelatin mixture over peaches.
Chill for several hours.
May be prepared, using graham cracker pie shells.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: confetti dip
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients in double boiler until thick. Remove from heat and cool.
Whip until creamy; add cream cheese and beat again until creamy.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Salt to taste and whip again.
Serve with chips and vegetables.

title: quick cheese cake pie - graham cracker crust
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and 1/2 cup of the milk.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Beat slowly, just until well mixed, about 1
minute.
Do not overbeat!
Pour at once into graham cracker crust.
Chill 1 hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chews
directions: Melt chocolate chips and condensed milk over low heat, stirring continually.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and cracker crumbs; cool.
Drop 1 teaspoon per cookie on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, no longer.
Remove instantly.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: jerred's millionaire pie(sugar-free)
directions: Mix the ingredients and press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Let cool.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all ingredients except noodles and sour cream. Put in crock-pot.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours or high 4 to 6 hours.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: citrus cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and cream cheese; mix well.
Blend in eggs, juice and rind.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix well. Chill several hours.
Shape into balls about 1-inch in size.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Indent center and fill with marmalade.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: north louisiana chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in 2 quarts salted water until tender.
Take off bones and do not put back in stock.

title: chicken crepes
directions: Beat Egg Beaters and milk together.
Add flour and beat well. Let the batter stand, but beat again before cooking.
Heat a crepe pan or a small nonstick pan until hot.
Pour about 2 tablespoons of the batter into the pan.

Tilt the pan to coat the whole bottom. Cook about 1 minute or until the underside is lightly brown. Turn the crepe and brown the other side for about 10 to 20 seconds. Remove and cool before filling. This should make about 15 crepes.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Take out of freezer 5 hours before serving.
Chip up with fork and add 2 bottles of ginger ale.

title: 7-up roast
directions: Mix all together and pour over roast.
Bake at 225° to 250° for 4 hours or in crock-pot on low for 6 to 7 hours.
Cooking in crock-pot makes roast real tender.
Serve gravy over a bed of rice.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil, then add flour, crushed pineapple and pecans.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Make syrup by bringing above ingredients to a boil. This quantity syrup is for approximately 1 1/2 quart rectangular baking dish.
Bake sweet potatoes (may use canned), peel, slice, and arrange in baking dish.
When syrup comes to boil remove from heat and pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake in oven 350° for approximately 30 minutes, basting occasionally until syrup thickens and potatoes are glazed.
Can do add a touch of cooking sherry when making syrup. This isn't necessary, but it does enhance the flavor.

title: old fashion coconut cake
directions: Sift cake flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream Crisco until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually until all is used; add egg whites, one at a time and beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and milk gradually, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add extract and beat 2 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven.
Bring to a boil, coconut juice and powdered sugar.
Spoon over each layer as you frost your cake.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Ritz crackers; sprinkle crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
In mixing bowl, mix the sugar, flour, cocoa and salt by hand or sift.
Separately beat eggs; add buttermilk and oil.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and butter well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add salt, flavorings and flour.
Mix well.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chili sauce.
Shape into ball.
Chill.
Pour half bottle of chili sauce over crab ball before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain between paper towels.
Layer sausage on bottom of casserole. Put cheeses on top, then the green chilies.
Combine eggs, milk and flour until well blended. Pour liquid over the mixture.
Decorate top with strips of green chilies.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown onion and meat in hot fat.
Add beans and soup; mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Mash potatoes and add milk, egg and seasonings.
Put on top of meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian supper casserole
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Stir in rice and ground beef.
Cook, stirring constantly, until meat is brown.
Remove from heat; stir in spaghetti sauce mix, then water and tomato sauce.
Return to heat.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust. I put pie crust in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with top crust.
Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: special mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat with bell peppers, large onion, chili powder, red pepper and garlic salt.
Mix Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of mushroom soup, refried beans and milk.
Add to meat mixture and mix.
In a casserole dish, layer chips (any kind).
Pour meat mixture over chips and mix.
Add cheeses and picante sauce over dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: mary's breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage until it crumbles.
Drain on paper towels.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add potatoes and cook until tender, stirring often.
Return sausage to skillet.
Pour eggs over potatoes and sausage.
Use a spatula to draw it across bottom of skillet until egg forms large curds.
Cheese may be added at this time.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Combine egg and milk.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix until flour is well moistened.
Do not overmix.
Fold in raisins and apples.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Bake for 20 minutes in 375° oven.
Yields 12 muffins.
Serve hot.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in saucepan; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter and the vanilla.
Stir until melted.
Add oatmeal.
Drop on cookie sheet. Set until firm.
For quicker results, refrigerate.

title: italian love cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix Ricotta cheese, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Spread on top of cake and bake for 55 minutes at 325°.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars thoroughly.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Mix in oats and nuts.
Shape into rolls; wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.
This can be made ahead and frozen until ready for cooking.

title: snickers pie
directions: Combine marshmallows, candy bars and milk in double boiler and melt.
Cool.
Whip whipping cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Finely chop onion, garlic and green pepper.
Brown same in a little olive oil.
If using bacon or sausage, brown with the onion, garlic and green pepper.
Open puree, tomatoes and paste and put into large pot.
Rinse cans with a little water and add; add the browned onion, garlic, green pepper, etc.
Add all spices. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer about 6 hours.
Wine or additional water may need to be added.
Tastes better if left to sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: salmon rice bake
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and microwave on High 5 minutes. Stir.
Cover and microwave on High until rice is done or tender, 6 to 7 minutes longer.
Stir before serving.
Put Velveeta cheese on or in for something different.

title: fruit squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except topping.
Spread 3/4 of batter in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or cookie sheet. Spread filling, then drop rest of batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 43 minutes.

title: deluxe pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add vanilla.
(Total beating, 10 minutes.)
Add cake flour, alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Pour batter into well-greased 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until cakes tests done.
(If you use a dark-colored fluted tube pan, reduce temperature to 325°.)
Cook in pan on rack 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Makes 12 servings.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and oats.
In a large bowl, cream margarine at medium speed with an electric mixer. Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Scrape down sides of bowl and then add egg whites and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add the flour mixture, raisins and blend gradually at low speed until combined.
Drop by 2 teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet, coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Put on wire rack to cool.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: special scalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute
onions until transparent. Remove onions from pan and brown bread cubes in butter.
Mix ingredients together and bake in greased casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: clam casserole
directions: Beat eggs in casserole dish.
Add milk, clams, crackers and salt. Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with cottage cheese.
Drain juice from pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate for 1 hour and it is ready to serve.

title: chocolate sugar cookies
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir 1 cup sugar into melted chocolate mixture until well blended.
Stir in egg and vanilla until completely mixed.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt. Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: oriental dip
directions: Chop green onions and water chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients. This is very good served with dip-size chips.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Drain oysters and save juice.
Combine crackers and onion to melted butter.
Arrange in layers, oysters on bottom of casserole, ending with crumbs on top.
Add 1/4 cup of oyster juice to milk and pour over top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Put peppers and pealed onions through food chopper.
Add salt; cover with boiling water, and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain liquid and discard.

Add vinegar and sugar to vegetables, bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes, ladle into hot canning jars; adjust lids at once, process in boiling water bath (212 degrees f.) for 5 minutes. Remove jars from canner and complete seals.
Yields 6 pints.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Place bread in greased 2-quart baking dish. Press down gently. Sprinkle with raisins. In small bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in whipping cream and syrup. Whisk together eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and salt. Add to cream cheese mixture. Pour evenly over bread. Lightly press bread into mixture with spatula. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. Remove from fridge 30 minutes before baking. Bake, covered, for 25 minutes at 375°. Uncover. Bake 20 minutes longer until center is set and top is golden brown. Serve with maple syrup. Serves 6.

title: irish whole wheat breakfast bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Sieve the flour, salt and baking soda into a mixing bowl and mix well. Using a large wooden spoon, add the buttermilk gradually (about 3/4 cup), until you have a soft, but not too wet, consistency. Use quick cutting strokes for mixing; do not beat or form a batter.

title: topsy turvey
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix dry ingredients, except 1/2 cup sugar. Add margarine.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Add fruit on top and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: knorr spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach until dry.
Mix all ingredients well (except bread).
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut center out of bread; cut into bite size pieces and place around loaf.
Put dip in center of bread and serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine and graham crackers.
Mix well and press in 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: party punch
directions: Combine juices and sugar; chill.
Just before serving, you might want to add strawberries.

title: sauteed squash
