directions: Slice zucchini and squash.
Saute onion and garlic in hot oil. Add squash slices and Italian seasoning.
Saute until squash is tender.

title: microwave apple butter
directions: Place in covered microwave-safe bowl.
Cook on High for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring every 3 or 4 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 10 x 13-inch pan. Mix together flour, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup milk. Pour over can of peaches in pan.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring until well combined.
Alternating between the two, gradually mix in flour and cream until thoroughly blended.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extracts.
Spoon into a greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool on a rack before removing from pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening and sugar together.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to mixture, alternating with milk and eggs. Beat until creamy.
Add flavoring and mix well.

title: beef pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake pie crust 10 minutes.
Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix soup, eggs, salt, pepper, onions and milk; add beef and cheese.
Pour into pie shell; cover edges with foil. Bake 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: recycled pickles
directions: Pour brine off pickles and rinse.
Slice then put back in jar and cover with cold water.
Let stand overnight.
Drain the next morning.
Bring to boil sugar, vinegar and spices.
Boil a few minutes.
Pour over sliced pickles.
Allow to stand.
That makes recycled pickles.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls (walnut size). Freeze.
Bake frozen at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Makes about 60.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Blend butter, sugar and flour.
Add beaten egg yolks, juice and rind of 1 lemon and 1 cup milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes, then down to 325° for 25 minutes.

title: fat-free chocolate therapy cake
directions: In a medium bowl, add ingredients, one at a time, stirring well after each addition.
After adding Marshmallow Creme, mix until the marshmallow lumps are gone.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan that has been lightly coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 servings at less than 1/2 gram of fat each.

title: creamy mocha fudge
directions: Dissolve coffee granules in hot water in a large saucepan; add semi-sweet chocolate morsels and sweetened condensed milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until morsels melt.
Spread into a lightly buttered 8-inch square pan or baking dish; sprinkle evenly with 1/4 cup chopped pecans.
Gently press pecans into fudge.
Chill until firm.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Crumble corned beef into well-greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Spread dressing and then sauerkraut. Cover with cheese. Toss bread cubes or crumbs with the melted margarine and spread over the top of the casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate chip ice cream pie
directions: 1. Coat bottom and sides of an 8 inch pie plate lightly with butter.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Bring
sugar,
milk,
vanilla, cocoa and margarine to a boil. Cook 1 minute. Set aside to cool.

title: french market doughnuts(beignets)
directions: Put the warm water into a bowl and then sprinkle in yeast. Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, evaporated milk and eggs. Gradually stir in 4 cups flour and beat with wooden spoon until smooth and blended.

title: tortis
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Then add hot water until it forms a ball.
Roll out and dip in hot Crisco until brown and not too crisp.
Then fill with meat and beans, taco sauce (that has been mixed in with meat while cooking) and cheese.

title: club day turkey or chicken and dressing
directions: Mix together bread cubes, melted margarine and water.
Put 1/2 in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together poultry, onion, celery, mayonnaise and salt.
Put over the stuffing.
Put last 1/2 of stuffing over meat mixture.

title: tootie bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Partially slice bread loaves.
Cut Swiss cheese in triangle slices.
Place cheese in between slices.
Put foil on cookie sheet and bread.
Mix and spread like icing on a cake on top and sides:
softened butter, onion, mustard and poppy seed.
Cut bacon into small pieces and place top of bread.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: confetti rice
directions: Tear assorted greens such as romaine, endive, butter lettuce and spinach into bite size pieces.
Put into a glass bowl and toss.
Serve with honey Dijon dressing.

title: glorified fruit
directions: Drain
oranges, pineapple chunks and cherries. To juice, add 4 tablespoons Tang and pudding. Bring to boil. Add oranges, pineapple and cherries. Add bananas, just before serving.

title: onion cough and cold syrup(home remedies)
directions: Shell and wash corn. For every cup of corn, use 1 level teaspoon of soda.
Put corn and soda in a big kettle and cover with water.
Boil slowly for 6 hours.
Drain and cover with fresh cold water. The hulls of the corn may be rubbed off easily now between palms of hands.
Boil for 45 minutes longer, changing the water 3 times.

Season the last water with salt and it is ready to use. Some people add a little sugar or molasses to the last water. Twelve cups of corn will make 2 gallons of hominy and it may be cold packed for future use.
Hominy is delicious served as a hot breakfast cereal with brown sugar and cream, as a side dish with meat or fried.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed except chocolate mixture and roll into small ball.
Chill for about 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and 1/4 pound paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip bonbons in the chocolate mixture and place on wax paper.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-boiled eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash. Mix yolks and other ingredients together.
Refill egg whites.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients for 2 minutes in saucepan.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper; let harden.

title: holiday eggnog bread
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well. Combine eggnog, oil and egg and add to dry ingredients, stirring just until blended.
Pour into greased 9x5 inch loaf pan.
Bake in 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Place in bottom of pie crust.
Mix Veg-All, soup and
milk.
Pour over chicken.
Put top crust on and seal.
Make holes in top.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown at 400°.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix all together. Bake exactly 15 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool and cut into squares.

title: applesauce cake
directions: You can put candied pineapple, dates or other fruits you choose.

title: cheese ring
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix everything together with hands.
Form into whatever shape desired (example:
a ring, heart, etc.).
Fill the center with strawberry preserves.
(Can be left in a ball in refrigerator until ready to be formed.)

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together the first 2 ingredients.
Add the oranges, pineapple and walnuts.
Fold in the Cool Whip.

title: mock steak
directions: Mix hamburger, water, cracker crumbs and salt.
Pack in pan or make roll.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and brown meat.
Cover with mushrooms, steak sauce, water and flour.
Bake 1 to 2 hours.

title: gourmet chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken; cut into pieces.
Mix all soups and broth.
Add touch of paprika and pimento.
Simmer until hot.
Add chopped chicken.
Add chopped boiled eggs.

title: apricot tarts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure flour by dipping method.
Mix flour and salt; cut in butter.
Sprinkle with water and vanilla; mix well with fork.
Using half the dough at a time, roll out to 1/16 inch thick on cloth covered board, generously sprinkled with sugar.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch squares.
Spread 1 level teaspoon of filling in center of each square.
Bring corners to center; seal together. Place sealed side up or down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and spread in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
In same bowl (don't bother to wash) mix eggs, brown sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, coconut and nuts.
Spread mixture on first layer and bake another 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares when cool (small squares). Batch can be doubled and baked in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil. Add eggs, flour, bananas and vanilla. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: robbie ray's methodist cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine cream cheese and oleo and mix well.
Add sugar and cream mixture until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and salt; beat mixture for 3 minutes.
Add flavoring and beat mixture for 2 more minutes. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and place in a cool oven. Turn oven to 300° to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Combine soup, relish, onion, brown sugar, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce in saucepan; mix well.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except crab and cheese.
Carefully fold in crabmeat.
Turn into baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle on Cheddar.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: gram's doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, cream and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll on floured board.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in hot deep fat.

title: charlotte's taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain well and let cool.
Layer ingredients in an extra large bowl as follows:
meat, peppers, onion, tomatoes and sprinkle bag of cheese over all of the tomatoes.
Cut lettuce into bite-size pieces and add to bowl.
When ready to serve, crush bag of Doritos and sprinkle over lettuce.
Add dressing and mix well.

title: eat dirt!
directions: Crush Oreos in blender or processor.
Cream together margarine, cheese and sugar in small bowl.
In large bowl, blend milk, pudding and Cool Whip until thick.
Add cheese mixture. Blend well.
Pour mixture into pot, starting with Oreos and layer alternately with pudding mixture, ending with dirt.
Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Mix the last 3 and pour over.
Toss and refrigerate.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix cheese in lightly.
Add milk slowly, just enough to hold dough together.
Roll out and cut biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes, until brown, on a greased cookie sheet.

title: top of stove cookies
directions: Put oleo, sugar, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil exactly one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper and let sit until firm.

title: egg foo yong
directions: In skillet, heat 1 tablespoon salad oil.
Cook and stir green pepper and onion until tender.
Stir in shrimp, bean sprouts, water chestnuts and soy sauce; heat through.
Remove from heat. In bowl, beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in shrimp mixture.
In skillet, heat 1 tablespoon salad oil.
Pour egg mixture into hot skillet from a ladle or cup to form patties about 5 inches in diameter.
When patties are set and brown, turn to other side to brown.
Serve warm with Hot Soy Sauce.

title: rice pudding
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs, then blend in milk, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Stir in cooked rice and raisins.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Set baking dish into another baking dish, then add water to larger baking dish until 1/2 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean. Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup cookie crumbs for top.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.
With electric mixer, blend pudding, milk and vanilla.
Add ice cream and mix well.
Spread over cooled crust.
Let set until firm.
Cover with whipped topping and sprinkle with 1/2 cup cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: waldorf party salad
directions: Combine fruit, marshmallows and nuts; toss lightly.
Combine whipped cream and salad dressing.
Fold into fruit salad.
Chill.

title: chuck wagon salisbury steak
directions: Measure corn flakes.
Crush them to one cup.
Place crushed cereal in bowl.
Add egg, 1/3 cup of
barbecue sauce, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Add ground beef.
Mix only until combined. Shape into 4 oval patties, about 3/4-inches thick.
Place in single layer in shallow baking pan.
Brush patties with remaining barbecue sauce.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 25 minutes.

title: quick bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, spices and vinegar.
Slice thin fresh unpeeled cucumbers.
Pack into jars with onions, if onions are desired.
Fill jars with boiling syrup.
Put immediately into boiling water for 5 minutes.

title: cranberry daiquiris
directions: In blender, blend rum, liqueurs and juices.
Chill, covered, for 1 to 3 hours.
Blend again at high speed for 10 seconds.
Pour into 4 well-chilled stemmed glasses filled with ice cubes. Garnish with cranberries.

title: spinach-apricot salad
directions: Chop apricots in half.
Pour boiling water over apricots; let stand 30 minutes.
Drain.
Remove stems from spinach.
Wash, dry and tear into bite size pieces.
Combine vinegar and preserves in blender; process until smooth.
As blending, add oil through opening in lid.
Combine salad and dressing.
Serve at once. Serves 8.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries and bananas and mash.
Add pineapple and mix together.
Refrigerate.

title: teriyaki hamburgers
directions: Shape meat into 4 patties.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl, stirring well.
Brush on patties.
Place patties on lightly greased rack of a broiler pan.
Broil 4-inches from heat until desired doneness.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add raisins, chopped walnuts, melted butter and applesauce.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch or 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with butter icing; sprinkle with shredded orange rind.
Decorate with nuts, or eat without icing.

title: orchid salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: kartoffel (potato) latkes
directions: Press out the liquid from the grated potatoes and discard. In a medium size bowl, combine the grated potatoes with the mashed potatoes, eggs, salt and pepper.
Shape the mixture into the desired size pancakes and fry in hot fat in a large skillet over medium-high heat until brown and crisp on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: stuff
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Cook onion in with it.
Add soup and cook on medium-low about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook your macaroni.
When it's done, drain and add it.
Also add the rice; stir it all up.
Put in a baking dish.
Put cheese on top; cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave cherry crunch
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple in square glass cake pan. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over top.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Drizzle butter over pecans.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes, turning at least once.

title: raspberry glaze pie
directions: Glaze:
Mix 1/2 cup berries, cornstarch, sugar and water.
Cook until clear and thick.
Remove from stove and add butter and lemon juice.
Let cool.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles, drain almost but not all, liquid off and add browned ground beef, soup, salt and pepper.
Cook until desired thickness.
Let individuals spoon amount of sour cream desired on their serving.

title: fudge
directions: In a pan on low heat, melt chips with milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and vanilla.
Put in an 8 or 9-inch buttered dish.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix meal, oil, eggs and corn; fold in sour cream.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 425° for around 20 minutes.
Test in the middle with a toothpick to be sure it's done.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chuck wagon baked beans
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours.
Great beans!

title: pull apart coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan thoroughly.
Arrange frozen roll balls on bottom of pan (all of them).
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons butterscotch regular pudding mix (save rest) over rolls.
Melt 1/4 pound oleo. Add packed brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well and drizzle over dough.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans and 1/2 cup raisins over rolls. Cover with towel and let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May need to cover with foil last 10 minutes of baking.

title: chicken breasts with dried beef
directions: Arrange dried beef in a shallow pan.
Wrap a strip of bacon around each chicken breast.
Arrange over beef.
Spread the soup and sour cream mixture over the chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for two hours.
Increase heat to 350° and bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: smoked turkey wings or legs and string beans
directions: Start cooking beans in water. When half cooked, add smoked turkey for seasoning of beans and finish until beans are firm and tasty. Smoked turkey is fully cooked and seasons the beans with little fat. You can cut off meat and distribute among beans before serving.

title: whole wheat angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and buttermilk.
In another bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and sugar.
Cut in butter and add yeast.
Knead slightly and roll the dough out 1/2-inch thick on a floured surface.
Cut with a biscuit cutter and bake on a greased cookie sheet at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: fresh mushroom creme soup
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter or margarine and saute mushrooms for about 5 minutes over medium heat.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, slowly melt the rest of the butter or margarine and add the flour. Mix well.
Gradually add the chicken broth, half and half, lemon, mushrooms and parsley.
Simmer over low heat until ready to serve. Do not boil.

title: "almost" stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients in a rice cooker.
Set on "cook" setting. When rice cooker switches to warm setting, stir and allow to set for 10 minutes.

title: blackberry delight salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Soften cheese in 4 tablespoons of hot mixture.
Add frozen berries, nuts and cheese to cooled gelatin.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 8.

title: white cake dessert
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 12 minutes.
Spread vanilla pudding on cake.
Spread pineapple on top.
Add Cool Whip to top.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry
hamburger;
add
onion
and green pepper.	Lightly simmer.
Add other ingredients.
Cook 1 hour at 350° or put in crock-pot and simmer low.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and margarine.
Add vanilla, lemon and sugar. Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Begin with flour and end with flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then at 300° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: oatmeal filled cookies
directions: Blend shortening with brown sugar.
Sift flour and soda; mix with oatmeal.
Blend dry mixture and vanilla into brown sugar and shortening, working into dough with hands.
Press 1/2 of mixture in the bottom of a well-greased pan.
Add filling, then other half of dough on top.

title: quiche
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter,
then beat eggs.
Mix together with flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Then add spinach and cheese.
Mix together.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Place into bowl with other ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Shape into small meatballs.
Fry.

title: grilled hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine unsweetened pineapple juice and salt in a shallow dish; mix well. Add chicken, turning to coat. Cover and refrigerate chicken for several hours, turning occasionally.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and set aside to cool.
Spread cookie dough on a greased pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 min.
Cool.
Whip cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with any fruit (strawberries, kiwi, bananas, and drained peaches).
Pour orange juice mixture over fruit. Refrigerate and cut into small pieces.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine butter, sugar, salt and vanilla; cream until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour.
Pinch off small pieces of stiff dough and flatten into circles on ungreased baking sheet, or shape into 1-inch ball.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until creamy tan in color.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar again.
Makes about 5 dozen rich crisp cookies.

title: flavored hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir until well blended.
Store in airtight container.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in pan.
(I use a skillet with a valve top lid.)

title: aunt shirley's walnut pound cake(125 years old)
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice, broth, soup, 1/4 cup of water and onion.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Place on top of soup mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes or until tender.

title: easter eggs
directions: Combine first
5 ingredients adding enough milk to make stiff, creamy
mixture.
Form into egg shapes, adding shredded coconut, nuts,
candied cherries or peanut butter, as desired. Place on plate
and refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Melt package of Baker's chocolate in double boiler.
Dip each egg, turning until completely covered.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: hearty casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off grease.
Add stewed tomatoes and mushrooms.
Let simmer on low heat.
Cook noodles in another pan until tender.
Layer noodles in bottom of casserole dish.
Slice cheese in thick slices and layer over the noodles.
Pour beef, tomatoes and mushrooms over cheese.
Put in oven at 325° and let cook until cheese starts bubbling to the top.

title: lipton pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into thin strips 2 inches long.
In a large skillet, heat shortening and brown meat, turning frequently.
Stir in soup mix and water.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in peppers and simmer 10 more minutes or until meat is done.
Blend cornstarch with water; stir into skillet.
Cook while stirring until thickened.
This is good served with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: real easy toffee candy
directions: Put sugar and oleo in microwave bowl (butter the rim of the dish
to
prevent boiling over).
Pour water around to wet sugar. Microwave on High 8 to 11 minutes or until a light tan color.

title: tomato goulash(serves 2 to 3 hungry people)
directions: Note:
Can be made with 1 1/2 pounds of lamb.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Parboil chicken and pork until tender.
Remove chicken and pork from bone and shred in small pieces into the crock-pot. Cover with entire bottle of barbecue sauce.

title: old fashioned pecan cake
directions: Cook the cake mix according to instructions on the box.
Set off to cool.

title: peanut fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a pan.
Cook to a soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow whip.
Beat until stiff enough to pour in a 6 x 10-inch pan.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix together and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Use meringue icing.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar together. Stir into mixture of flour, baking soda and milk. Grease baking dish and add mixture. Pour juice from cherries into bowl and add 1/2 cup sugar to juice. Place cherries on top of batter and then pour juice over cherries. Cook 55 minutes at 375°.

title: walnut cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together into large bowl.
Add Crisco, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes. Fold in walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan on rack.

title: easy triple-chocolate fudge
directions: Line an 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil or waxed paper, letting liner extend a few inches above pan on 2 sides.
Stir condensed milk and butter in a medium-size saucepan over low heat until butter melts.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips and stir until melted and smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spread in prepared pan and refrigerate 8 hours, or until firm enough to cut.
Lift foil by ends onto cutting board.
Cut fudge in 1-inch squares.
Store airtight with waxed paper between layers.

title: batter dipped fish
directions: Place the milk in a shallow dish, such as a pie plate.
Add the flounder and soak for 5 minutes.
Dredge the fish in the flour to coat.
Then dip in the egg whites.
Dredge in the bread crumbs. Dip the fish in the egg whites again and then into the bread crumbs again.
Coat a slotted broiler pan with nonstick spray.
Place the fish on the pan, sprinkle lightly with paprika and pepper.
Spray fish lightly with nonstick spray.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes. Serves 4.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cut corn from cob or use creamed corn.
Beat eggs.
Add milk. Cream butter, corn and seasonings.
Turn into well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs over top.

title: jo's basic sugar cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients into creamed mixture, using dough hooks (heavy duty mixer) or good muscle.
Dough will be stiff. Roll into balls the size of a walnut and press with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for a couple of minutes before removing to wire rack to cool.

title: vegetable and cheese casserole
directions: Combine 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions with other ingredients in a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: blackberry cake
directions: (I only use cinnamon.)

title: puppy chow for people(party mix)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Mix the last 3 ingredients and melt to blend.
Use microwave to melt; place on High for 1 minute intervals until well blended.
Pour melted ingredients into the dry ingredients and mix to coat the cereal.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and Kool-Aid in 2 quarts water.
Add remaining water and pineapple juice in mixture.
Put in carton and freeze.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in slightly salted water.
Drain.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt, pepper, tomato soup and green pepper.
Put carrots in container; pour mixture over them.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Lightly toss together the potatoes, celery, cucumber, olives and onions.
With a fork, thoroughly but carefully, blend in the dressing mixed with the oregano.
Cover the salad. Chill for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour once, measure add soda, salt, spices and sugar and sift into mixing bowl.
Add oil, eggs, water and pumpkin in order given.
Add nuts and pour into two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans lined with brown paper.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.
Remove from oven; allow to stand in pans 10 minutes, then remove paper.

title: homemade shake and bake for chicken
directions: Combine.
Dip chicken in milk, then in Shake and Bake.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Open tuna and drain off oil.
Finely chop the eggs, onion and apple.
Mix together with tuna.
Add sour cream and mayonnaise to the mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste desired.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind ham, then mix with sausage or pork, bread crumbs, eggs and milk; mix well.
Make loaf and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Sift flour and spices and add to creamed mixture.
Stir soda into applesauce and mix well.
Add applesauce to mixture and mix.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 full with batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken chips and cheese casserole
directions: In a medium bowl mix soup, chilies and 1 cup water.
In casserole dish layer chips to cover the bottom.
Spray with Pam first.
Layer 1/2 the chicken, 1/2 the tomatoes and 1/2 the cheese.
Layer again, then pour the soup mix over the top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: spicy vegetable gumbo
directions: Cut the onion, carrots and celery into bite-sized pieces. Put in a large soup pot along with 1 can chicken broth and minced garlic. Cover and simmer until vegetables are softened (about 10 minutes). Chop the cabbage, squash, zucchini, broccoli and cauliflower into bite-sized pieces and add to the soup pot. Stir in 2 cans chicken broth, tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, rosemary and Creole seasoning. Mix well and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 45 minutes. Season with black pepper before serving. Makes 6 (2 cup) servings.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill before serving.
A good dip for raw vegetables.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Use black olives, pepper rings, sour cream as toppings when serving.
Brown meat; drain.
Add seasoning and tomatoes.
When hot, add soups; heat again.

title: chicken rice scallop
directions: Alternate layers of rice, chicken, pimento, peppers and mushrooms, ending with rice.
Brown bread crumbs in butter and spread over top. Thicken broth with flour and pour over all. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: childrens' delight casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in buttered 1-quart casserole dish at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cherry fruit rolls
directions: Place 2 tablespoons of pie filling in center of tortilla. Roll up.
Place seam side down on baking sheet sprayed with Pam. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Serve warm.

title: toll house pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until blended.
Beat in butter.
Stir in semi-sweet morsels and walnuts. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: green beans and tomatoes
directions: Cook pepper, onion and bacon together 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain excess fat from bacon.
Add tomatoes.
Chop and mix well.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add beans and seasonings.
Blend thoroughly and add mushrooms.
Place in a greased casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry clafouti
directions: Heat
oven to 350°.
Grease square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Beat eggs, milk, flour, granulated sugar and vanilla with hand beater until smooth.
Spread cherries in dish. Pour batter over cherries.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.
Each serving is 170 calories.

title: egg souffle
directions: Remove crusts from bread and cube.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt cheese with butter.
Pour evenly over bread. Beat eggs with milk.
Pour over cheese mixture and refrigerate. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300°.

title: egg casserole
directions: In a large baking dish, place a layer of rolled soda cracker crumbs. Moisten well with half the cream sauce, next a layer of cheese, then a layer of grated eggs.
Repeat these layers and be sure the crumbs are well moistened. Top with buttered crumbs. Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.

title: pudding fruit
directions: Drain fruit and save juice. Add enough orange juice to the saved juice to make 4 cups. Cook pudding according to directions, using juice instead of milk. Cool. Mix with fruit and let set 2 hours. Add bananas before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together corn oil,
sugar	and
eggs.
In separate bowl, sift together flour,
baking
soda,
salt
and cinnamon. Beat together with the sugar
and
egg
mixture.
Stir
in the vanilla, mixing well.
Add
the
carrots, walnuts, coconut and pineapple. Mix well.
Pour
batter into a greased and floured 9 or 10-inch Bundt pan.	Bake
at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool on rack; remove.

title: barbecue cup
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and onion.
Separate dough into biscuits.
Place each biscuit in ungreased muffin cups, bottom and sides.
Spoon meat mixture into cups.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: ben frandsen's barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Rub mixture into meat of choice; let stand 2 hours at room temperature or overnight, chilled, before cooking.
Baste with the sauce.

title: easy as pie
directions: Let Cool Whip and cream cheese soften.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and concentrated beverage in mixing bowl.
Stir or mix until smooth.
Fold into graham cracker crust and chill.
When you are ready to serve, top with additional fruit or nuts.

title: baked stuffed pork chops
directions: Prepare chops by cutting slit along fat side and into chop to form a pocket.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Prepare egg by mixing egg, mustard and milk.
Using 1/4 cup dressing, stuff tightly into pocket and press fatty edges together to close.
Dip each chop into egg wash, then flour.
In very hot oil, fry until brown.
Remove and drain.
Place in large casserole.
Cover with thin gravy.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove foil and bake uncovered an additional 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add oil and other ingredients and mix. Bake in 350° oven 55 minutes.
Grease and flour pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: quick sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef in an 8 to 10-inch frying pan on medium-high heat for 5 minutes or until meat begins to brown.
Break meat into fine crumbs as it cooks.
While beef cooks, chop onion and green pepper. Add onion and pepper to beef along with chili powder.
Cook, stirring, for about 15 minutes or until onion is translucent.
Stir in sugar and soup.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes more, until hot and bubbly.
Add salt and pepper to taste; keep hot.
Split sandwich buns crosswise.
Lightly butter cut sides.
Toast in a broiler or toaster oven.
Spoon hot Sloppy Joes mixture over toasted buns. Serve hot.

title: fruit pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple and add enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Add cherries and pineapple.
Stir in sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cook until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Then add food color, vanilla, chopped nuts and diced bananas.
Stir until blended.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat chili and cream cheese together until cream cheese is melted.
Put in casserole and add Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted.
Serve with tostitos or taco chips.

title: broccoli-stuffed sole
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
For stuffing, drain broccoli, press out excess liquid.
Combine egg, half of the cream cheese and the Parmesan cheese.
Stir in broccoli and stuffing mix.
Spoon 1/4 of the mixture onto the end of each fillet.
Roll up; secure rolls with wooden toothpicks.
Place in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: cracker barrel's hash brown casserole
directions: Mix milk, broth, 1 tablespoon butter, garlic, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Heat 1 tablespoon butter in skillet.
When hot, stir in hash browns and onion.
Add broth mixture and cook about 7 minutes.
Add cheese and bake in 425° oven for 45 to 60 minutes. Serve hot.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool and pull meat from bones. Chill broth, skim fat from broth and skin the chicken.
Combine vegetables, potatoes, mushrooms & bouillon with broth.
Cook until potatoes are fork tender.
Add chicken and pour into square baking pan.
Top with biscuits and bake 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Add eggs.
Mix broth with soup. Pour over chicken.
Add vegetables.
Melt butter.
Mix flour with milk.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: potato ala
directions: Boil potatoes in skin; cool.
Peel and grate; set aside.
Heat soup and butter until butter melts.
Add cheese, sour cream and onions until cheese melts.
Mix with potatoes.
Pour into a large casserole; bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken with brandy sauce
directions: Brush chicken with oil; season.
Cook under broiler.
Cook sliced mushrooms in butter until tender.
Increase heat.
Pour in brandy and cream.
Boil rapidly, stirring until sauce reduces to coating consistency.
Adjust seasoning.
Pour over chicken.
A quick and easy recipe.

title: ever crisp sweet pickles
directions: This solution should be hot enough to melt sugar.
After covering with solution, let cucumbers soak in mixture overnight.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, sour cream, onion, half of taco seasoning, half can of soup, 1 cup of cheese and salsa.
Place 1/3 cup of mixture on each tortilla and roll. Place, seam side down, in sprayed 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over tortillas.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serve with lettuce, cheese and salsa.

title: neiman marcus treat
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press in 9x13-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown bacon and onions.
Set aside and scramble eggs.
Add mushrooms, browned meat, rice and crumbled bacon.
Stir.
Add soy sauce until brown (about 4 tablespoons).
Mix well.
Quick, easy and very good!

title: chicken almond
directions: Combine soups, cheese and wine in large, shallow baking dish. Add chicken, bone side down.
Cover pan with foil and bake in moderately slow oven at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove foil.
Add sliced almonds and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Dissolve coffee in boiling water; add sugar and vanilla bean or extract.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Cool.
When cold, add vodka. Stir.
Store in large bottle or jug for about 30 days.
Serve as a dessert sauce or as a liqueur.

title: kraut salad
directions: Cut up and drain well your Chinese bean sprouts and sauerkraut.
Add green pepper, celery and pimentos. Finally add Wesson oil and sugar.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heavily grease and flour a 10 inch tube pan.
In a mixing bowl or on a piece of wax paper, stir together both flours.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients. Prebake pie crusts 5 minutes. Add mixed ingredients to pie shells and cook about 30 minutes or until done. Makes 2 pies.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into large casserole dish.
Sprinkle crunched corn flakes over the top.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: sue's favorite dip
directions: Mix the sour cream with the dry Italian dressing.
Chill for about 2 hours.
This can be made the day before needed.
Serve with fresh vegetables or even potato chips.
This is so easy and everybody loves it!
Makes 2 cups.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs.
In greased loaf tin, put eggs, milk, salt, pepper, crumbs and then corn.
Bake about an hour at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese first, then mix 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar and 2
eggs and beat. Follow until all ingredients are gone, seventh egg last.
Bake for 3 hours at 300°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cheese which has been softened to room temperature.
Whip furiously with wire whipper until well blended with Jell-O.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Drain pineapple and add enough water to juice to make another cup of liquid.
Add to Jell-O.
Add partly thawed strawberries, pineapple and nuts.
Put in a large casserole and refrigerate.
When firm, cover tightly with Saran Wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Saute onions in butter.
Remove skillet from heat and stir in flour.
Gradually stir in broth until well blended.
Add half and half.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Mix in cooked rice, chicken, pimento and seasonings.
Blend and put in large baking pan.
Sprinkle toasted almonds over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: southwestern corn soup
directions: Melt butter and saute carrots, onion and celery until tender. Add garlic and cumin; heat 1 minute.
Add broth, pepper and corn. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Add almonds.
Process in blender or food processor.
Garnish with sour cream, Cheddar cheese, cilantro and green onion.
Serve with pita bread wedges, toasted with cheese, green chilies and black olives.

title: bean 'n bacon soup(to can)
directions: Cook vegetables, except onions, until soft.
Cut up bacon and fry; remove from grease and cook onions in grease until tender. Mix all ingredients; heat until it simmers, then put in jars. Process 1 hour in pressure cooker.
Soup is rather thick, so broth or water may be added.
Makes 16 to 18 quarts.

title: pineapple-raisin drops
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together. Add egg and vanilla. Stir in pineapple. Sift together all dry ingredients. Add to mixture. Beat until smooth. Stir in raisins. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. When golden brown, cool on rack. Makes 36 cookies.

title: jo anne's peanut butter cup heaven
directions: Mix melted margarine and flour until a paste consistency. Pat on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (or until lightly brown). Let cool.

title: broccoli with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Cook onion in 4 tablespoons butter in a skillet until tender.

title: presidential cinnamon glazed almonds
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place butter on 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Place in oven to melt butter, about 7 minutes.

title: sugar cookies(rolled)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and almond.
Add flour and baking powder; mix well.
Do not chill.
Roll out and cut.
Bake in 400° oven 8 to 10 minutes.
Decorate with icing. Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix and form into small balls.
Put in shallow pan and cover with 1 can tomato soup and 1 can water.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Baste occasionally.
Makes 10 medium size servings.

title: apple muffins(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 12 muffin cups with cooking spray. Combine apple and honey.
Set aside.
Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in the center.
Combine egg, milk and margarine.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened. Stir in apple mixture.
Spoon batter into muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.
Contains approximately 118 calories each.

title: crock-pot stuffed cabbages
directions: Mix into meat the rice, onions, peppers, salt and garlic powder.
Precook cabbage and cut around core of cabbage until leaves fall off.
Form meat in shape of balls the size of cabbage leaves. Fold in and roll.
Put in 6 1/2-quart crock-pot on high. Cover with some tomato juice.
When juice cooks down, drain grease and add rest of juice.
Cook 5 to 6 hours until done.

title: chris' oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars
and
shortening.	Add
egg and beat well. Add oil and dry ingredients and mix together.
Add cornflakes, nuts and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a
lightly
greased cookie sheet and press down with a fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Do not brown them.

title: dream salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed.
Combine with sugar and salt.
Put in flat Pyrex dish to cool, then add apples, bananas and pineapple. Let set.

title: fruchtebowle
directions: Mix the fruits together and cool it for ca. two hours.
Before serving, add champagne and water.
If you want, you can put some sugar into the bowl.
Prost, Fuur Wohl!

title: herb cheese spread
directions: Add all ingredients together and blend until smooth.
Place in container and chill.

title: graduation drink
directions: Simmer sugar and water over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Chill. Add remaining ingredients.

title: party pink salad
directions: Drain pineapple and put juice and marshmallows in pan over low to medium heat.
Stir until melted.
Stir in dry jello and remove from heat.
Cool while whipping cream.
Stir pineapple, cottage cheese and whipped cream into jello mixture.
Pour into buttered mold and refrigerate.

title: pork chop dinner bake
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet and brown chops on both sides. Butter a large baking dish which has a well-fitting cover.
Arrange potatoes and onions in layers, sesaoning with salt and pepper as you go.
Place browned chops on top; salt and pepper them.
Mix Worcestershire sauce, mushroom soup and milk and pour over all. Cover tightly and bake at 375° for about 50 minutes, or until chops are very tender.
Remove lid for the last few minutes for browning. Yields six servings.

title: pizza pasta
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Brown beef, onions and Worcestershire sauce.
Add green pepper, garlic salt and Ragu sauce; simmer 15 minutes.

title: fluffy pumpkin pie
directions: Blend sugar and spices.
Stir pumpkin and beaten eggs into sugar mixture. Add milk, stirring well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Lower oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 20 minutes longer or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: coke chocolate cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Combine next 4 ingredients. Combine the two.
Grease 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Put miniature marshmallows in dish.
Pour mixture over and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flavoring and sour cream.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cranberry, cherry and walnut chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat. Cook for 20 minutes, stirring well.
Cool chutney to room temperature. Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Chutney thickens as it cools and will keep for up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: thyme and cheese biscuits
directions: Grease a cookie sheet and set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder, herbs and cheese in a large mixing bowl, using a fork.
Cut in butter.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Add milk and stir until dough holds together.
You may add more milk if necessary.
Drop by large spoonfuls on the cookie sheet an inch apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: grandma's gelatin salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar, boiling water and gelatine. Stir until completely dissolved, then let cool. Mix together cooled Jell-O, crushed pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts. Let set until the consistency of egg whites. Fold in whipped topping. Place in a mold or dish and refrigerate. This is very good and can be made several hours ahead of serving time, or even day before.

title: turkey noodle soup
directions: Place turkey, water, celery, onion, bouillon, salt, pepper and bay leaf in large kettle. Cover and simmer about 1 hour. Remove carcass.
Add carrots, peas and green beans.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Add meat from carcass.
Heat soup. Add noodles and cook 10 minutes.
Melt butter in small pan. Add flour and stir constantly until flour is browned. Stir into soup. Boil 5 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Take peanut butter and mix with margarine and sugar until smooth with a wooden spoon.
Form small balls and then put in refrigerator on wax paper for 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry beef and sausage. Pour off grease. Add onion and chili pepper. Put layer of meat, layer of cheese, layer of meat and layer of cheese. Pour eggs and milk mixture over dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel
directions: Boil butter, sugar and syrups for five minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and pour slowly over the popped corn mixing well.
Bake in 250° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring every few minutes to prevent top from burning.
When it's as crisp as you want it, pour out on waxed paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: sour cream dinner rolls(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until butter melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°. Combine yeast and 1/2 cup warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir together yeast mixture, sour cream mixture, eggs and flour in large bowl until well blended.
Chill, covered, 8 hours.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Stir together sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan.
Blend milk and egg yolks together.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture. Cook over medium heat.
Blend in butter and extract.
Stir in 3/4 cup flaked coconut.
Sprinkle remainder of flaked coconut over whipped cream on pie.
Chill pie for 2 hours prior to serving.

title: date cake
directions: Dates,
nuts and cherries may be left whole if desired. Sift dry ingredients together 3 times, sifting over fruit and nut mixture
the
last time.
Add beaten yolks.
Fold or work stiffly beaten
egg
whites
to which vanilla has been added. Let
stand for thirty minutes and mix again.
Use heavy waxed paper, grease and
line pan.
Cover top of cake and place pan of water
under cake.
Bake at 250° for over 2 hours.
Remove cover
from
top
of cake
during
last 15 minutes of baking. After
cake is removed from oven, cool thoroughly in the paper in which
it
was baked. Then wrap securely in a second layer of heavy paper (waxed paper is preferred) and tie with twine.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix mustard and jelly.
Beat with a whisk.
Put on stove and bring to a boil.
Pour over wieners that have been cut in small pieces.
Pour into crock-pot and cook on high for 3 or 4 hours.

title: tasty toss up
directions: Prepare Creamettes rotini according to package directions; drain.
In a large bowl, combine rotini, tuna, cucumbers, tomato, celery, green pepper and onion.
In a small bowl, blend together Italian dressing, mayonnaise, mustard and seasonings.
Add to salad mixture.
Toss to coat.
Cover and chill.
Toss gently before serving.

title: canned vegetable soup
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes.
Add water, butter beans, sliced okra, small chopped carrots, chopped bell pepper, vinegar, sugar, chopped onion and corn (cut off cob).
Mix everything together; put into quart jars and cook on 10 pounds pressure for 25 minutes. Should make 8 quarts.

title: chicken spaghetti #3
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in butter.
Add dry seasonings and milk; stir in soup, pimentos and cheese.
Fold in spaghetti.
Boil chicken until tender; debone and set aside.
When mixing spaghetti with mixture, if it looks dry, add more broth (I use broth to boil spaghetti).
Pour in sheet cake size pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: meat loaf to can
directions: Cold pack 2 hours.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage until separating.
Saute onion in oil.
Cool. Line bottom of pan with cabbage leaves.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fastnachts
directions: Place flour in bowl; make well in center.
Soften yeast and 1/2 tablespoon of sugar in 1/2 cup milk.
Pour into flour.
Mix and let rise until light.
Add remaining milk, egg, salt, sugar and shortening.
Work into a dough.
Knead thoroughly adding more flour is necessary.

title: quick green beans
directions: If fresh beans, wash well, snip off stems, then sliver, French-style.
Put fresh beans into a pan, adding boiling water to not quite cover beans.
Cover tightly; bring to boiling over high heat, then remove the lid and cook until crisp-tender.
(For canned beans, drain and cook the liquid down to half over high heat.) For all, turn a few times during cooking; you want to prevent scorching as the liquid cooks away.
When finished, there should be barely a spoonful of liquid in the pot.
While the beans are cooking, saute pecans in butter over low heat until very crisp.
When beans are tender-crisp, add 2 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper to taste, then the Accent.
Add the pecans; toss slightly.
Serve at once.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter dandy
directions: Cream together eggs and sugar.
Add milk, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: ground beef-cabbage casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, cook cabbage in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Add butter, salt, rice, onion and egg to cabbage; mix thoroughly.
Place layer of cabbage in casserole.
Then a layer of ground beef.
Repeat layers.

title: spicy chicken and pasta
directions: Mix margarine, soup and cheese, then add tomatoes, onion, Worcestershire and chicken.
Add cooked vermicelli.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions for use in casserole. If salt added to water, more will not be necessary in sauce.
Make cream sauce by melting butter and adding flour slowly, stirring constantly.
Add milk, a little at a time.
When sauce is thick and smooth, put in 3/4 of cheese.
Cook and stir until melted. Add mustard and salt, if needed.

title: quick fruit dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan (place in oven).
Combine milk, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Stir slightly to moisten ingredients.
Pour mixture evenly onto melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit evenly over batter.
Push apples into batter slightly.
Sprinkle cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: black cherry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in the hot water.
Stir in the juice from the cherries.
Add prepared cherries.
Stir in pineapple and pecans. Pour all into an 8 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate until well set. Then add topping.

title: linguine and shrimp in cheese sauce
directions: Saute garlic in butter for about 1 to 2
minutes.
Add milk, Ricotta cheese, shrimp and peas.
Cook until smooth.
Add Tabasco. Cover and cook on low heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese. Pour sauce over cooked linguine.
Toss well to coat.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Toss chicken, celery, water chestnuts, grapes and pineapple carefully.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and seasonings; mix into tossed ingredients.
Add eggs and sprinkle with almonds. Serves 8 to 10.

title: dixie pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
I use Ritz.
Makes its own top crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until light brown.
Good for Christmas.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and other ingredients, except crusts.
Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie crusts and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda and cocoa.
Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and milk into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Frost while warm and sprinkle with coconut or nuts.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in unbaked 9-inch pie shell at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Can substitute fresh strawberries, raspberries or rhubarb for peaches.

title: mystery meatloaf
directions: Take 2 cups of flour mix with 1 gallon of sugar.
Put in the oven for 12 hours at 250°.
Shape it as a banana then let it cool for about 1 hour.
Sprinkle yellow sprinkles until no fudge is showing.
On top of the cake put 5 chocolate brownies.
In the center put a single strawberry then crack 2 raw eggs on top. Put in the refrigerator for 2 days, then serve.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients, pour into pie crust.
Freeze until firm.
To make recipe low fat, use low fat milk, Cool Whip and pie crust.

title: chicken-potato casserole
directions: Blend flour into butter; slowly add broth, stirring constantly.
Add salt and cheese.
Cook until smooth.
Add all other ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Place in a casserole dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Dice beef and green onions.
Combine with cream cheese until well blended.
Form into ball.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in double boiler and mix together until smooth.
Start with 3 1/2 cups powdered sugar until you see how thick the mixture is.
It should be thick like cookie dough batter. If it needs to be thicker, add more powdered sugar, a little at a time.
Do not use more than the original 4 cups of powdered sugar!

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together crushed grahams, butter and sugar.
Press into oblong dish.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: glazed lemon cake
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Combine soda and vinegar;
mix well.
Stir into batter.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack 15 minutes. Remove from pan.
Combine lemon juice with powdered sugar; drizzle over cake while it is warm.

title: papa's potato, bacon and egg burritos
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Fry bacon and potatoes.
Chop bacon into pieces.
Crack eggs in bowl; add salt, pepper, potatoes and bacon.
Stir all ingredients in bowl.
Pour into frying pan and cook until eggs are done.
Spoon egg mixture on flour tortilla and fold.
Serves 5.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Mix all this together, but sugar.
Make balls out of this, then bake.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: asparagus-mushroom soup
directions: *Can substitute 10 ounces frozen cut asparagus, thawed for fresh asparagus.

title: german chocolate cheese pie
directions: Heat water and chocolate in small saucepan over low heat until chocolate is just melted.
Stir constantly.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes.
In large bowl of electric mixer, beat cream cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla and salt.
Slowly beat in chocolate to cheese mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until very thick.
Fold in whipped topping.
Turn into crust.
Freeze 4 hours or overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in skillet.
Simmer 20 minutes. Cool.
Toss remaining ingredients except Doritos and Catalina dressing in large serving bowl.
Add hamburg mixture and mix well. Just before serving, add crumbled Doritos and dressing.
Toss well.

title: gazpacho
directions: Mix the V-8 juice, stewed tomatoes, olive oil and Worcestershire sauce in a soup pot.
Stir in about 1/3 of the chopped onions and peppers, all the garlic and the black pepper to the pot.
Occasionally stir and heat the mixture over a medium burner until it begins to simmer.
Remove the pot from the heat. Add the remainder of the vegetables and wine to the mixture. Refrigerate for about 2 hours.
Serve.

title: new orleans-style broiled chicken
directions: Wash and dry the chicken.
Sprinkle both sides of each piece with salt, pepper, rosemary, parsley and lemon juice.
Preheat the broiler and broiler rack.
Melt the butter over low heat in a small saucepan.
Pour half the melted butter on the skin side of the chicken pieces.
Then place them skin side down on the hot broiler rack.
Pour the remaining butter over and broil, about 7-inches from the flame, for 20 minutes on each side.
Serve with the juice and butter that collect in the broiling pan poured on the chicken.

title: tarheel corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Pour about 2 tablespoons oil into a cast-iron skillet.
Sprinkle in a little corn meal.
Set on burner at medium heat until corn meal is golden brown.
Combine all ingredients and mix until blended and pour into prepared pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Grate onion, celery and carrot.
Boil in a 3-quart saucepan with enough water to cover potatoes.
While boiling, add parsley, salt and pepper.
When potatoes are cooked, add milk, soup and butter.
Simmer to blend flavors.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Cook until beginning to thicken.
Add egg yolks and cook until done.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: In a large saucepan melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Add onion, green pepper and celery; saute over medium heat.
Cook until celery is almost tender (about 5 minutes).
Remove vegetables. Mix in macaroni and chopped olives.
Set aside.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in saucepan; cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add jello to above; mix thoroughly.
Arrange whole strawberries in pie shell.
Pour mixture over berries.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pork tenderloin with plum ketchup
directions: In processor, process plums, onion, garlic and ginger until finely chopped.
In saucepan, combine plum mixture, sugar, vinegar, cinnamon, salt and pepper flakes.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes, until thickened (about 2 cups). Remove to bowl; let cool.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook beans, ham, onion and salt according to directions on package of beans.
When done, drain and add rest of ingredients. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cushaw pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust and bake for 15 minutes at 400°, then lower temperature to 350° and bake for about 45 minutes or until set in center of pie.

title: to die for dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and spread into cake pan. Sprinkle bacon bits on top. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Serve with Triscuits crackers.

title: turkey chowder
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until soft but not brown, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add flour. Blend thoroughly. Add broth and milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add carrots and heat to boiling point. Add cheese and heat until melted. Season. Add turkey bits and parsley.

title: bean and turkey soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Yields 9 1/2 cups.

title: chicken with swiss cheese
directions: Place
chicken on
bottom
of
dish.
Put
cheese
over chicken.
Heat soup with 1 can water and pour over top.
Mix 2 cups stuffing with 3 tablespoons butter.
Pour over top.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: lemon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins.
Combine first six ingredients in bowl.
Stir together egg, yogurt, butter and lemon juice.
Add to dry mix.
Put in tins; bake 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and place on wire rack.
Prick with fork and pour glaze on warm muffins.

title: vegetable relish salad
directions: Heat oil, vinegar and sugar.
Let cool.
Pour over mixed ingredients and refrigerate.

title: melt in your mouth blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar until stiff.
Cream shortening and 2 cups sugar and add dry ingredients alternating with the milk and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Fold in blueberries.
Put into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Cook and chop chicken; add celery, cheese and 1/2 of almonds. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together the mayonnaise and soup. Add to other mixture.
Pour all into buttered dish.
Mix 1/4 stick butter with cornflakes and the other 1/2 of almonds.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: diabetic cornbread
directions: Bake at 400° until done.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Crush Ramen noodles.
Place in a colander.
Pour 2 cups boiling water over noodles to soften slightly. Combine drained noodles, cabbage, onion and chestnuts in a large bowl.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix breadcrumbs with Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken in butter and coat with crumbs.
Place in baking dish with pieces touching. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese and drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean salad
directions: Clean beans and cut in half, steam until tender Let cool at room temperature).
Dice onion, cut tomatoes into chunks.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl add salt & pepper to taste. Refrigerate overnight.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients.
Sometimes I add a teaspoon of vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet bread and butttr pickles
directions: Bring to a boil.
Add cukes and onions.
Return to heat and bring to a boil.
Let cool and put in canning jars.
Stir occasionally.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Pour milk over oats and let stand 2 minutes before mixing other ingredients in.
Preheat lightly oiled griddle to 370° to 390°.
Add all remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Mixture will be thin.
Yields 16 pancakes.

title: ron's cashew chicken
directions: Blend cornstarch and 2 tablespoons soy sauce in bowl.
Mix in chicken; set aside.
Mix remaining soy sauce, wine, sugar and vinegar; set aside.
Heat oil in uncovered wok at 375°.
When hot, add pepper flakes; stir-fry until black, 10 seconds.
Add chicken; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove chicken with strainer; set aside.
Add green onions and ginger root; stir-fry one minute.
Add chicken; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add wine mixture; stir-fry 1 minute.
Stir in cashews.
Serve with hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Add coconut and vanilla to cake mix and prepare as directed on box. After cake cooks and still hot poke holes in top of cake. Boil together 1/2 to 1 C. milk, 1 tsp. vanilla and 1/2 C. sugar. Pour over cake. Let cool completely. Add Cool Whip on top and add coconut to top of Cool Whip.

title: grandma van drie's goulash
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery; drain.
Combine ground beef, onion, celery, tomatoes and tomato soup in Dutch oven. Slice Velveeta; lay on top of mixture.
Simmer on stove for approximately 1 hour.
Or, put in crock-pot for 5 to 8 hours on low.
About 20 minutes before serving, boil macaroni; drain and mix with tomato-beef mixture.
Serve with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Add flavoring.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook hamburger until done; drain off all fat.
Spread 1 can of crescent rolls in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan or dish.
Mix hamburger, taco sauce, tomato sauce and refried beans together. Pour over rolls.
Sprinkle cheese over top mixture.
Cover with second can of crescent rolls.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: easy apple surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Soften butter.
Add sugar and egg.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Combine with butter mixture.
Add apples, walnuts and raisins.
Bake in 9-inch pie pan for 40 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine marshmallows with drained pineapple (reserve juice). Put in fridge overnight.
Combine the beaten egg, vinegar, sugar and flour; cook until thick.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Brown flour in bacon grease; it doesn't need to be very dark. Add water, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer in iron skillet about 45 minutes.
Add more water if necessary.
This gravy is delicious over grits or with biscuits.
I have used canned tomatoes so it doesn't have to cook as long.

title: swordfish deluxe
directions: Dredge fish with flour and press rosemary into the fish. Brush with oil. Place 5 tablespoons butter in a large skillet and add fish. Cook, turning once, until fish is flaky (about 15 minutes). Sprinkle with salt and remove to a hot platter. Add wine and remaining butter to skillet and heat; pour over fish.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine zucchini and onion in medium saucepan.
Add water to cover and bring to boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: I use two bread pans for this recipe and line them with foil to get them out easily.
Pour half of batter in pans.
Pour half of topping, then rest of batter and rest of topping.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix salad oil, sugar and eggs. Add flour, soda, nuts, salt and vanilla. Stir in apples. Bake in Bundt pan 60 to 90 minutes at 350°.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper; set aside. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Set aside.

title: creamed dried beef(amish)
directions: Again be forewarned and be sure to cover the roast sufficiently with foil.
Spread half of the mushroom soup and half of the onion soup mix on each side.
Wrap securely and place on wire rack or better still put it in a baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours in a preheated oven.
Mashed potatoes should go so well with this because you already have an excellent seasoned gravy.
Serves 4.

title: hickory nut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and syrup, stirring well.
Fold in eggs and flour.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: marshmallow nut puffs
directions: Heat cream; add vanilla.
When hot, dip 1 marshmallow in cream until outside is soft.
Roll in finely ground pecans and coconut. Flatten slightly and chill.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Cut onions into 1/4-inch slices.
Separate into rings.
Place in bowl with cold water to cover; let stand for 15 minutes and drain.
In a bowl, combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dip rings into evaporated milk.
Coat with flour mixture.
Cook in hot fat until brown, turning often.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: cornish hen teriyaki
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients for sauce.	Marinate hen in sauce for
1 hour.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour, basting with sauce 2 or 3 times.
Cut Cornish hen in half to serve.
Medium fryer may be substituted for Cornish hen.
Yields 2 servings.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Brown chops in skillet sprayed with PAM.
Place in 9 x 14 baking dish or pan.
Mix soups together (no water).
Pour over chops.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° over for one hour.

title: wassail drink
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil. Add orange juice, real lemon, shake of cloves, ginger and cinnamon. Serve hot.

title: broccoli and rice dish
directions: Cook broccoli.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix broccoli, onion, rice, soup, Cheez Whiz and egg.
Put in large baking dish. Garnish with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fajitas
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Marinate in fajita marinade for 1 hour.
Saute peppers and onion in oil or margarine until soft. Add a little marinade to the vegetables as they cook.
Cook meat until done.
Heat tortillas and keep warm.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until done.

title: rock cookies
directions: Cut up all fruit and mix with apple juice.
Cream butter and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, alternating flour.
Add fruit, nuts, and spices.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10-15 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: quick baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise. Brush cut halves with butter. Sprinkle with paprika, salt, butter and cheese. Place cut side down on well oiled baking sheet. Salt skin side of each potato. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until tender.

title: grandmother's chocolate cake
directions: Beat together applesauce and sugars.
Add Egg Beaters, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to liquid ingredients.
Stir.
Add water.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and water.
Add well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to other mixture.
Roll and cut in desired shapes.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for about 8 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil well for batter.
Spread half of batter over nuts.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Save 2 teaspoons of this mix for topping.
Sprinkle the rest over batter. Add the rest of the batter.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup nuts and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot ham buns
directions: Combine all ingredients, except buns.
Mix well.
Split the buns.
Spread each with ham mixture.
Wrap each in foil. Refrigerate until ready to heat.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Melt butter.
Mix together the flour, sugar, cocoa, salt (if desired) and melted butter.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Dissolve soda in boiling water and add to batter.
It wil be very thin.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and garnish with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spoon bread
directions: Blend milk, salt, butter and bring to a boil, slowly stirring in sifted cornmeal until blended thoroughly.
Remove from heat and stir in egg yolks, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve at once while hot.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add to flour and salt.
Mix together.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Drizzle melted oleo on crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: oven chicken and rice
directions: Coat chicken with seasoned flour; brown well in shortening. Combine rice with other ingredients.
Place in shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Top with chicken and cover.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Sift next 3 ingredients and add to creamed mixture, then add: oatmeal, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Butter bottom of small glass, dip in sugar and flatten cookies slightly.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Pour olive oil over pasta.
Blend sugar, white vinegar, salt, garlic powder and mustard.
Mix and pour over pasta.
Add onion, cucumber, pimento and parsley. Will keep for 1 week.

title: judy wainscott's chocolate fudge
directions: Mix together cocoa and powdered sugar; set aside. Melt margarine and Velveeta cheese in the microwave. Mix them with the powdered sugar and cocoa. Put in a greased pan.
Let it cool and cut in pieces. Add nuts if desired.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chill and serve on party rye bread or crackers.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: spice cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
(Multiply 5 times to feed 120.)

title: minted punch
directions: Simmer rinds with water and sugar 5 minutes. Cool and squeeze rinds, discard. Add lemon and pineapple juice, color as needed and add flavoring. Add ginger ale, garnish with fresh mint. Serves 40.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Place broccoli in the bottom of dish.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Crumble crackers on the top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: toasted coconut cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour three 9-inch cake pans. Spread the coconut on a baking sheet and toast in the oven for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring about every 30 seconds, until the coconut begins to brown slightly. Remove immediately from the pan to prevent further browning. Beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form. Set aside. In another bowl, cream together the butter, sugar, and extracts. Add the egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine the flour, baking soda, and salt and stir to mix. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk. Fold in the beaten egg whites and 1 cup of the toasted coconut. Spoon the batter into the prepared pans. Bake for about 25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of one of the layers. Remove the layers from the pans immediately and cool completely on rack.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Use corn cobs that you've cut the corn off for canning or freezing.
Cover with water and boil for 15 minutes or so.
Drain and strain liquid off.
Make from directions off of pectin.
Tastes similar to honey.

title: caramel pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, raisins, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and milk together.
Put in a greased baking dish.

title: hot five bean salad
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Salt and pepper; blend into drippings.
Stir in vinegar and water; cook and stir until boiling.
Stir in all beans.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn into serving dish.
Crumble bacon on top.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: grandma green's smothered potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, onion and bacon drippings in a heavy iron skillet.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on low heat, stirring often, until potatoes are well done.
Do not add water.

title: baked alaska
directions: Cut cake in two.
Spread ice cream between layers.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
