Fold in powdered sugar, salt and cream of tartar.
Coat entire cake with egg white mixture.
Bake in 450° oven for about 3 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute nuts in butter, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes or until toasted.
Set aside to cool.

title: chicken salad shells
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Press dough into mini muffin pans.
Makes about 3 dozen shells.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Fill with your favorite chicken salad.
(1 pound of chicken salad for 4 dozen shells).

title: farmer's market vegetable bowl
directions: Cut sweet red peppers in half lengthwise; remove and discard seeds and membranes.
Place pepper, skin side up, on a large baking sheet; flatten with palm of hand.
Broil 5 1/2 inches from heat 12 minutes or until charred.
Place peppers in ice water; chill 5 minutes.
Remove from water; peel and discard skins.
Cut into thin strips and set aside.

title: crescent turkey squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine (reserve 1 tablespoon) until smooth.
Add the turkey, salt, pepper, milk, chives and pimento together and mix well.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Cut off stems so the choke sits flat, snip off the spiny tip from each leaf and cut top of artichoke straight across.
Parboil the chokes for about 10 to 15 minutes, depending on size.
Drain and let cool enough to handle.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring to dissolve sugar; freeze.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Use juice including juice with water to make 3 3/4 cups of liquid.
Bring to a boil and pour over jello.
When jello cools and begins to set add:
Pineapple, sliced olives, and cherries.
Place in refrigerator.
Based on 8 to 10 servings.

title: meat loaf roll
directions: Rinse frozen broccoli under running cold water to separate; drain.
Mix hamburger, eggs, bread crumbs, ketchup, milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and oregano.
Pat hamburger mixture into rectangle, about 12 x 10 inches, on a piece of aluminum foil. Arrange broccoli on hamburger to within 1/2 inch of edges; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt.
Arrange ham on broccoli.
Roll up rectangle carefully, beginning at the 10-inch side and using foil to lift.
Press edges and ends of roll to seal.
Place on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Overlap cheese on top; cook just until cheese melts. (Center of meat loaf may be slightly pink due to ham.)

title: walnut-cranberry-mushroom stuffing
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.

Saute mushrooms, celery, nuts and onion for about 5 minutes (until tender and golden brown). Add salt, stuffing mix, parsley and cranberry sauce; blend well. Use to stuff turkey, chickens or your favorite vegetable.
Yields enough for a 6-pound turkey or two 4-pound chickens.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate overnight for best flavor. Great with all raw vegetables and chips.

title: curry dip
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend until smooth and mixed thoroughly.
Cover and chill well.
Keeps very well for several weeks.
Use as a dip for veggies or over baked potato instead of sour cream.
Delicious over cold poached salmon!

title: 3 way spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain off grease.
To meat mixture, add all other ingredients and simmer at least 4 hours.
The longer it cooks, the better the flavor.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles.
Top with raw chopped onions and lots of grated Cheddar cheese.

title: comet balls
directions: Melt marshmallows.
Put round toothpicks in malted milk balls. Roll milk balls in marshmallows. Roll in nuts, removing stick to cover completely.
Let cool on wax paper.
Eat!

title: taco meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients into bowl.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown. Serve on toothpicks.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat together the egg yolks, sugar and butter.
Add coconut, raisins and pecans.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; bake 40 to 45 minutes at 300°.

title: milk chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and salt in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Heat to boiling, then cook 9 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips, marshmallows, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into buttered pan and allow to cool.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Spread over the melted butter.
Pour fruit and juice over flour mixture.
Bake approximately 1 hour in 350° oven.
Crust will form over peaches.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix vegetables together.
Add as much grated Cheddar cheese and bacon bits as you like.
Add enough mayonnaise to coat.
Keeps well a day or so.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Mix eggnog and ice cream together with wire whisk until desired consistency is reached.
Add Vernors while stirring. Serve.
(This is very rich probably better as an appetizer drink than as a meal beverage.)

title: pita pizza
directions: Mix tomato sauce with oregano and basil.
Spread evenly on pitas.
Top each with mushrooms, chopped pepper and onion and sprinkle with grated Parmesan.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Place pizzas directly on racks.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Serve hot. Contains 268 calories each.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk; add Cool Whip.
Layer crackers in greased dish.
Add a layer of filling, another layer of crackers, layer of filling and final layer of crackers.
Spread frosting over crackers.
Refrigerate 1 to 3 hours.
Serve cold.
Easier to frost when cool.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat shortening over low heat until melted; remove from heat.
Mix in brown sugar, egg and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased square baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cut into 1 3/4-inch squares while warm.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen cookies; 120 calories each.

title: quick ice cream loaf
directions: Add syrup to cream.
Whip until stiff, then chill.
Place ice cream blocks on platter, narrow ends together.
Frost sides and top with whipped cream.
Press ladyfingers around sides. Sprinkle top with chocolate curls.
To serve, slice like a loaf cake.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: slime
directions: Mix ingredients and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Cool, then add food coloring.

title: mondel bread(jewish)
directions: Mix all together.
Grease 4 aluminum ice trays.
Pour batter into each.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from trays.
Cut on slant (slice) and toast in oven with cinnamon and sugar sprinkled on each side until brown and dry, about 10 minutes.

title: mints
directions: Mix together. If too stiff to work, add a few drops of milk. Add a few drops of food coloring to whole batch or part of batch. Shape into balls in palm of hands. Design with fork by pressing down on platter. Let set a few minutes, overnight, or freeze for future use.

title: hot pepper pie
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Brown ground beef.
Add tomato sauce, peppers and cheese.
Let simmer while you prepare pie crust, top and bottom.
Fill pie crust with mixture, then put top on.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 20 minutes.
Pull pie out and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sweet potatoes, until resembles coarse crumbs.
Add sweet potatoes and sugar.
You just have to add 1/2 cup sugar and mix in well and taste, if you like them sweeter, add more sugar.
Go by your taste.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Make chocolate cake mix according to package.
Make 4 layers. Combine coconut, marshmallows, 1 cup sugar, 1 cup milk, and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Boil 5 minutes after marshmallows melt.
Set aside to cool.
Combine 2 cups sugar, cocoa, 2/3 cup milk, margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and pour in small glass bowl and beat for 3 minutes.
Add 1 tablespoon peanut butter.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Put filling between layers and icing on sides and top.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir in crushed potato chips and flour.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until edges of cookies are lightly browned.
Makes 8 1/2 dozen.

title: easy bake everything
directions: Beat thoroughly margarine, sugar, egg, peanut butter, water and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Blend in oats and chocolate chips.

title: pound cake(nut cake)
directions: Combine sugar, butter and Crisco.
Cream together.
Blend in the 4 eggs.
Add everything else.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: gram's salad dressing
directions: Put in bottle; shake and keep in fridge.

title: swiss cheese cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine water and butter in a saucepan. Bring to boil.
When water boils, quickly add flour.
Remove from heat.
Beat with wooden spoon until it forms a ball and does not separate.
Remove from heat and add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in grated cheese.

title: rocks
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add unbeaten
eggs.
Stir in dates and walnut meats.
Add sifted flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cannoli(dessert)
directions: Mix flour, shortening, salt and sugar.
Add enough wine (can use water if desired) to make a stiff, but workable, dough.
Roll into a ball and let stand 1 hour.
Roll out dough 1/8-inch thick. Cut into 5-inch squares and wrap the dough around a short cannoli tube so that the opposite corners meet.
Fry in deep fat one at a time until golden brown.

title: easy apple dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together with mixer until creamy and smooth.
Dip is ready to use or can be chilled.
Dip your favorite apple slices into the dip.
Tastes just like caramel apples. Great fall treat!

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and oil. Add the flour, salt, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add the nuts and chopped apples. Bake in greased pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients, then roll into ball.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll in chopped walnuts or pecans for decoration.

title: pound cake
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam; coat with granulated sugar.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, or until done. Cool 10 minutes; turn onto plate.
No icing needed.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, butter and 3 teaspoons sugar and pack in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Beat remaining sugar into cream cheese.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel layer and refrigerate.
Mix Jell-O, water and strawberries and refrigerate until almost set, then spoon strawberry mixture over cream cheese layer and refrigerate.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: In a heavy 3-quart saucepan, brown the meat over medium-hot heat, breaking it up. Spoon excess fat in a small bowl.
Mash 4 cups beans and liquid into paste.
Add to saucepan with remaining ingredients. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to moderate and simmer 30 to 40 minutes until cabbage is tender.
Makes 7 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix everything except stuffing mix and melted butter which you put on top.
Put mix, then melted butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix lard and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Then add soda, baking powder, pineapple and flour and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet and bake at 350°.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In mixing bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco until mixture resembles coarse meal. In another bowl, combine egg and milk.
Beat lightly with fork. Add to flour mixture all at once stirring enough to make soft dough.
Turn out onto floured board.
Knead 15 times.
Roll out to 1-inch thickness.
Cut biscuits with biscuit cutter.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until brown at 400°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread, put in greased baking dish.
Brown link sausage. Add to bread.
Add cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour egg mixture on top of other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: party lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until tender. Drain and rinse. Mix soup, milk, salt and poultry seasoning.
Heat until hot, but not boiling.
Set aside.

title: scallops with glazed garlic and champagne sauce
directions: Place garlic in small saucepan of water.
Bring to a boil. Drain.
Return garlic to pan. Add fresh water and bring to a boil again. Drain and set aside.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan, cover bottom with oil evenly.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add rest of oil; mix just until blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beet salad and dressing
directions: Mix jello as usual, using the beet juice and pineapple juice as part of the liquid.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need one clean flowerpot and 1 bouquet of silk flowers.

title: caramel creams
directions: Caramelize 1/2 cup sugar; when thin, add to above mixture. Cook until forms soft ball in cold water.
Let cool.
Add vanilla and beat until creamed.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: tom jones shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash shrimp; spread in a single layer in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients except butter.
Pour over shrimp; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir several times while cooking. Peel when cool enough to handle.
Use French bread for dipping in sauce.
Serves 2.
Great with corn-on-the-cob.

title: oreo delight
directions: Soften ice cream or yogurt.
Crush cookies.
Mix all ingredients well; pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refreeze until firm.

title: butterscotch sheet cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, 4 eggs and pudding in large bowl.
Butter cookie sheet.
Pour batter over it and even it out.
Sprinkle on sugar and butterscotch chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to the directions on box.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan.

title: low-fat baked apples(this easy fruit dessert has no added sugar.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove core from apples, leaving 1/2-inch of the core at bottom of the apple.
Peel top one-third of apple.
Arrange apples in baking pan.
Put 1 tablespoon of raisins in the center of each apple.
Pour water over apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until tender. Spoon liquid from pan over apples one or two times during baking. Makes 4 servings, 1 apple each.
Per serving:
105 calories, 0 g cholesterol, 1 g fat and 0 sodium.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Make sure all pieces of shell are removed from the crabmeat. Melt cheese and butter until soft. Stir in crabmeat.

title: ranch dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Great with chips and veggies.

title: hamburger steak in mushroom gravy
directions: Combine meat with egg, crumbs and seasonings with half onion soup mix.
Shape into patties and fry in oil.
Remove browned burgers.
Add flour to pan; blend in until browned lightly.
Blend in mushroom soup, water and remaining onion soup mix.
Cook 5 minutes.
Return meat to skillet and cook slowly for 5 minutes.

title: grandma's brownies
directions: Melt together butter, cocoa, oil and water.
Bring to a boil. Combine flour and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Add cocoa mixture and mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Pour onto deep cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat until smooth.
Dip apple slices in dip.

title: pot roast
directions: Put vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
Salt and pepper meat, then put in pot. Add liquid.
Cover and cook on low 10 hours or high for 5 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: 3 cheese lasagna
directions: Heat oil in a medium size saucepan over moderate heat.
Add the onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 3 to 5 minutes until onion is translucent.
Stir in tomatoes (break up with spoon), tomato paste, parsley, oregano, basil and 2 cups water. Reduce heat to low.
Simmer uncovered, about 25 minutes, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened.

title: clam sauce for linguine
directions: In skillet, saute garlic in oil.
Drain clams, reserving broth.
Add, stir and saute until cooked 3 minutes.
Add clear broth, wine, parsley, basil, oregano, pepper and cheese.
Cover and simmer at least 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked linguine with additional Parmesan cheese and pepper to taste.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Pour pizza sauce into bottom of the crock-pot.
Layer each of the remaining items.
Cook for 5 hours on low.

title: polish dinner
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together like meat loaf.
Core and parboil cabbage to loosen leaves.
Heap meat mixture onto cabbage leaf.
Roll.

title: "paximadia" - sweet rusks
directions: With electric mixer, beat eggs, sugar and lemon juice until all sugar has disappeared.
Add oil and beat again.
Add baking soda and beat again.
Gradually add flour and knead until a soft dough is formed.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in hot water.
Add all liquid ingredients.
Place dough in a large bowl and refrigerate (rising is unnecessary).
Pinch off amount needed to bake.
Bake for 40 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: date faces
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Cut slices while still hot and roll in powdered sugar.

title: mini cheesecakes(servings:  12)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line muffin tins with paper liners. Mix melted butter with cookie crumbs and press into bottom of each liner.
Whip together cream cheese and honey, then egg and vanilla until fluffy.
Divide evenly into liners.
Bake in center of oven for 12 minutes.
Do not remove.
Turn off oven and leave in unopened oven for another 12 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: chicken noodles
directions: Boil chicken and onion until done; remove chicken from broth to cool.
Add garlic powder and noodles to boiling broth.
Cook until done.
Add soups, cheese and chicken meat.
Can add extra cheese, if desired.
Boil until thickened.

title: chicken-dressing bake
directions: Toss stuffing with half of the soup, all the chicken broth and beaten eggs.
Spread mixture in a 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan. Top with the cooked, diced chicken (turkey).

title: day's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: strawberry-rhubarb ice milk
directions: *May use either Equal or Sweet One instead of sugar.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Cream margarine and confectioners sugar.
Add melted chocolate chips.
Beat with beaters on low.
Add vanilla and eggs one at a time.
Pour into cool baked pie shell or graham cracker crust and chill.
Before serving, whip the cream.
Serve in small slices with a large dollop of whipped cream.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix in bowl the water and yeast (you can use milk instead of water), sugar and salt.
Work in flour to thicken batter into stiff dough.
Let rise, then make into rolls.
Let rise and then bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: mama's peanut butter pie
directions: Cook pudding according to label directions.
Cream together peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly.
Set aside 2 tablespoons.
Press remaining mixture into baked pie crust.
Pour chocolate pudding over this and let chill until almost set.
Cover with Cool Whip topping.
Sprinkle on the remaining peanut butter and powdered sugar mix.
Keep refrigerated until serving time.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together well the first 7 ingredients.
Make into balls; brown lightly on all sides.
Simmer, uncovered, in sauce made of the catsup, grape jelly and Burgundy (optional).

title: biscochitos
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon; dip cookies in mixture before baking.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: In greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, mix the uncooked Minute rice, cream of chicken soup, onions, water, cubed chicken, salt and pepper.
Spread cream of mushroom soup on top.
Sprinkle Durkee French fried onions on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice and broccoli hot dish
directions: Mix rice and soup.
Top with broccoli and then cheese.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pollo criollo rapido
directions: Place cooked rice in a lightly greased 8-cup baking dish. Saute green pepper, onion, celery and garlic in butter until tender in a large saucepan. Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese. Pour mixture over rice, spreading evenly. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes until bubbly hot. Serves 4.

title: steak casserole
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces.
Put into pan.
Layer onions and potatoes over steak.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Uncover.
Sprinkle cheese over potatoes.
Bake until melted.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs and other ingredients listed.
Pour into 2 well-greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: "that" dip!
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger and add onion.
Cook until brown. Add mushrooms.
Add oregano, salt and pepper.
Pat cream cheese on bottom of microwave-safe dish.
Cover with hamburger mixture. Cover with pizza sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Microwave until cheese melts.
Dip with crackers.
This one's great!

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Combine raisins and carrots.
Add mayonnaise and mix well.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in margarine and coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all and place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Mix 2 Tbsp. sugar and 1/4 tsp. cinnamon and sprinkle on top and bake for an additional 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: troy's cheesy potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine potatoes with enough water to cover.
Bring to boiling and cook, covered, for about 12 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Drain off water.
In a 4-quart Dutch oven, cook onion, celery and carrot in butter until tender. Stir in cornstarch.
Add the milk and bouillon granules to the cooked onion mixture.
Stir in potatoes.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add ham; heat through.
Serve topped with additional cheese.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add raisins and gradually stir in milk.
Spread in greased pan.
Mix brown sugar, butter and boiling water and pour over batter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until smooth.

title: hawaiian-style hot curried fruit
directions: Drain fruits (reserve 6 tablespoons of juice) and put in buttered glass baking dish.
Cut and arrange bananas on top. Combine and mix together the brown sugar, cornstarch and curry powder.
Add fruit juice and butter.
Pour mixture over fruits. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tortillas
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding water a couple of tablespoons at a time until dough is workable but not sticky.
Add a little more flour, if necessary.
Separate dough into 12 small balls.
Roll out into circles and cook in an iron skillet or griddle, turning to brown both sides evenly.

title: collard greens
directions: Place turkey in Dutch oven or large saucepan.
Add water, pepper pods and garlic.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 30 minutes.
Break off and discard stems of collards.
Wash leaves thoroughly.
Slice leaves into bite size pieces by rolling several leaves together and slicing in 1/4-inch strips.
Add collards, onion, celery, green pepper, sugar, oil, salt and pepper.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes or until greens are done. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: them things - debbra's dumplings
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together (except dumpling dough); place in the refrigerator for about 30 to 40 minutes. Place the dumpling dough circles out on the counter.
Wet the dough with your finger.
For each dough circle, spoon a teaspoon of refrigerated mix on the dough.
Fold the dough together and pinch until it sticks.
The dough package should have 36 dumplings.

title: ginger creams
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg.
Beat well after; add molasses.
Stir soda into warm water.
Add alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Spread with Powdered Sugar Icing.
Cut into strips 1 x 2-inches.

title: no flour date cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
(Batter will be thick.) Spread in square cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy lemon cheese cake
directions: Measure 1 cup dry cake mix, set aside.
Combine remaining cake mix with 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil.
Press in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan; bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine reserved mix, 2 eggs, sugar, cream cheese and sour cream.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes longer.
Cool.

title: diet millionaire pie
directions: Mix and pour into graham cracker crust.
It's ready!!

title: cheese and chile dip
directions: Combine lemon juice and bouillon granules; let stand a few minutes.
Add other ingredients and beat with mixer at medium speed until smooth.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: vietnam popcorn
directions: Mix ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over popcorn.
Spread on cookie sheet. Put in a 200° oven about 1 hour to dry.
Will keep in plastic bags a long time.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
(I use a small roasting pan and cover which works really well.)
Put in pan.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir a couple of times during baking.
Stir before serving.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti noodles; drain and cool.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix together mayonnaise, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, spinach and sour cream.
Add hamburger.
Stuff cheese mixture into manicotti tubes.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Pour Prego over top; sprinkle some oregano over sauce. Cover; bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake for 10 more minutes.

title: tomato filled squash
directions: Steam squash until tender (not overdone).
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds.
Combine remaining ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Spoon mixture into squash.
Top with bread crumbs, which have been slightly browned in butter. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: sweet-sour cabbage
directions: Clean off and slice cabbage.
Boil in 1/2 pan of water about 15 minutes until tender; drain.
Fry onion in bacon grease until tender.
Add drained cabbage.
Stir in brown sugar and vinegar on low heat.
Add more brown sugar or vinegar according to your taste.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple and cherries.
Add Coca-Cola to fruit juice to measure 2 cups.
Bring juice to a boil.
Dissolve gelatins in hot juice.
Let cool.
Blend 2 packages cream cheese into mixture.
Add fruit and cola mixture and nuts to congeal.

title: super beefy enchiladas
directions: Combine beef, 1/2 cup cheese and onions; set aside.
Combine soups and enchilada sauce.
Dip tortillas in hot oil and cook just a second to soften.

title: bean and rice soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except cilantro and rice in large soup pot and heat to boiling. Reduce heat to medium high and cook for about 2 hours or until beans are tender (you may have to add additional water if needed). Add rice and cilantro to soup and cook 5 more minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of casserole that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle dry soup mix on top of rice.
Place the chicken on top.
Mix the mushroom soup and water together and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: dill dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before using.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine lemon juice, butter, sugar and egg.
Cook until thickened.
Mix with fruits and marshmallows and refrigerate. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: delightfully different carrots
directions: Slice carrots and cook in lightly salted water until done. Drain and cool.
Combine the remaining ingredients; pour over carrots and marinate 24 hours.
Will keep up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: microwave snowballs
directions: In 2-quart bowl measure, combine crumbs, marshmallows, nuts, dates and milk.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes to soften marshmallows.
They will partially melt.
Stir to combine ingredients.

title: easy hollandaise sauce
directions: Heat butter until bubbly.
Meanwhile, in blender, place egg yolks, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Turn blender on and off quickly.
Next turn blender to high speed and slowly add butter very steadily in a thin stream.
Serve immediately.
(It's great served over broccoli, grilled tomatoes, asparagus, fish or on Eggs Benedict.)

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 2-quart shallow baking dish. Spread chicken and vegetables in prepared dish.
Stir soup and chicken broth in a small mixing bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Add pepper and then pour over chicken.
Combine recipe mix, milk and butter.
Stir until smooth and pour ingredients in a baking dish. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Grate cheese and mix with mayonnaise.
Add cooked noodles.
Crush Wheat Thins and sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken with mallet to flatten.
Place one slice of cheese and 1 slice of ham on each whole chicken breast.
Fold breast in half and secure with toothpick.
Coat each chicken bundle with bread crumbs.
Melt butter in pan.
Place chicken in pan and cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Turn once.
Baste occasionally.

title: pork sausage
directions: Grind pork and add ground beef and seasoning.
Stuff into casings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Dip caps in lemon juice.
Chop stems.
In a small saucepan, place butter, 1 1/2 tablespoons lemon juice, onion, garlic, oregano, salt and mushroom stems.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add shredded Swiss cheese.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together until well mixed.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: simple yeast rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add water and mix.
Cover bowl, when mixed, with plastic wrap and place in warm area.
Let rise 1 hour or until double in size.
Knead out on floured surface and cut out like biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Watch bottoms.
They brown fast.
Use top rack of oven, if possible.
